INSERT INTO `content` VALUES (1,'Content for Step1','<p>This is a test</p>','test, another tag, and more',1,1,'2017-09-18 13:22:43','2017-09-18 13:22:43','Some delicious content for step1',NULL),(2,'Content for Step1','<p>This is a test</p>','test, another tag, and more',1,1,'2017-09-18 13:22:57','2017-09-18 13:22:57','Some delicious content for step1',NULL),(3,'Content for step2','<p>Body of step2</p>','tag1 tag2',1,1,'2017-09-18 13:24:00','2017-09-18 13:24:00','Another description for step2',NULL),(4,'Data collection','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Data collection</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:53','2017-10-11 10:04:53','',NULL),(5,'Statistics','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Statistics</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Statistics are all around us. &nbsp;In fact it would be difficult to go through a full week without using statistics. Imagine watching a football game where no one kept score. &nbsp;<br>\r\nThe action itself might provide enough excitement to hold your attention for a while, but think of all the drama that would be lost if winning and losing were not an issue.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Imagine going to the grocery store and trying to find the best buy on a box of doggie treats for your dog, Fluffy. &nbsp;Without statistics this task would come down to simple guess work. &nbsp;You could never know for sure if you get the best (cheapest) treats for your rand. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Without statistics we could not plan our budgets, pay our taxes, enjoy games to their fullest, or&nbsp;evaluate classroom performance. &nbsp;Are you beginning to get the picture? &nbsp;<br>\r\nWe need statistics.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Two main statistical methodologies are used in data analysis, namely descriptive statistics and inferential statistics.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The most basic form of statistics is&nbsp;known as <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">descriptive statistics</span>. &nbsp;This branch of statistics lays the foundation for all statistical knowledge. &nbsp;This makes it quite important, but it is not something that you should learn simply so you can use it in the distant future. &nbsp;Descriptive statistics can be used now, in English class, in Mathematics class, at the football stadium and in the grocery store. &nbsp;You probably already know more about statistics than you think.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:53','2017-10-11 10:04:53','',NULL),(6,'Descriptive statistics','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Descriptive statistics</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Two main statistical methodologies are used in data analysis, namely <span class=\"PalAa\">descriptive statistics</span> and <span class=\"PalAb\">inferential statistics</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Descriptive statistics</span> refer to collecting, summarising and processing data to transform the data into information. &nbsp;Data can be <span class=\"PalAa\">collected</span> through surveys, <span class=\"PalAa\">summarised</span> via methods like calculating the sample mean, and <span class=\"PalAa\">processed</span>&nbsp;by&nbsp;presenting it in&nbsp;tables and&nbsp;graphs.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Inferential statistics</span> provide the basis for <span class=\"PalAb\">predictions</span>, <span class=\"PalAb\">forecasts</span> and <span class=\"PalAb\">estimates</span> that are used to transform data into knowledge.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit will focus on <span class=\"PalAa\">descriptive statistics</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:53','2017-10-11 10:04:53','',NULL),(7,'Video','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch this video on the importance of statistics:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/362.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:53','2017-10-11 10:04:53','',NULL),(8,'Key definitions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Key definitions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Radial is a company which advertises that its <em>XXX</em> tyres, generally known as <em>Triple X</em>, will complete at least <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(65\\Tsp000\\)</span> kilometres before one of the four tyres will no longer meet the minimum safety requirements. However, lately several complaints have been received that the tyres completed <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\Tsp000\\)</span> kilometres only and thus the&nbsp;minimum requirements were not met.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Radial sells directly to the public and it is company policy to keep a record of customers. &nbsp;They have been manufacturing tyres for the past two&nbsp;years.&nbsp; In the&nbsp;previous six months they had sold <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\Tsp600\\)</span>&nbsp;sets of <em>XXX</em> tyres. &nbsp;Radial feels that they do not have the time, personnel&nbsp;or money to locate and question all <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\Tsp600\\)</span>&nbsp;of their customers. &nbsp;They feel that if they question <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(80\\)</span>&nbsp;customers it should give them a good idea of what the actual situation is.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In other words, they will take a <span class=\"PalAb\">sample</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{80}\\)</span>&nbsp;out of the <span class=\"PalAa\">population</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{2\\Tsp600}\\)</span>. &nbsp;<br>\r\n<span class=\"PalAb\">Sample</span> and <span class=\"PalAa\">population</span> are words which are inevitable when we wish to obtain data.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the following definitions:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">A <span class=\"PalAa\">population</span> is the set of all the elements or items being studied.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In Radial&#39;s case the set of all <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{2\\Tsp600}\\)</span>&nbsp;sets of <em>XXX</em> tyres sold, is the <span class=\"PalAa\">population</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">A <span class=\"PalAb\">sample</span> is a representative group or a subset of the population.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{80}\\)</span>&nbsp;sets of tyres that Radial will investigate will form the <span class=\"PalAb\">sample</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">A <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">variable</span> is any property or characteristic<br>\r\n		that can be measured or observed.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A variable can take on a range of different values. &nbsp;For example, the distance completed with a set of tyres is different for each customer and therefore the observations vary continually. &nbsp;Distance completed is a variable.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">The <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">sample unit</span> is the item which is measured or<br>\r\n		counted with respect to the variable being studied.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We see that the members of a sample are the sample units. &nbsp;Radial&#39;s sample unit is a set of tyres to be measured for the minimum safety requirements.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:53','2017-10-11 10:04:53','',NULL),(9,'Index numbers','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Index numbers</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:53','2017-10-11 10:04:53','',NULL),(10,'Formula','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Formula</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A simple index involves one product only. &nbsp;A simple index is written as:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{\\PalBc{\\text{number}}\\text{ in }\\PalAa{\\text{given year}}}{\\PalBc{\\text{number}}\\text{ in }\\PalAb{\\text{base year}}}\\times100\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The formula for a simple index is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I_\\PalAa n=\\displaystyle\\frac{\\PalBc n_\\PalAa n}{\\PalBc n_\\PalAb0}\\times100\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">where</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I_\\PalAa n\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the index for the&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{n^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span> <span class=\"PalAa\">period</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc n_\\PalAa n\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the <span class=\"PalBc\">number</span><span style=\"color:#FF0000;\"> </span>in the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{n^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span> <span class=\"PalAa\">period</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc n_\\PalAb0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the <span class=\"PalBc\">number</span><span style=\"color:#FF0000;\"> </span>in the <span class=\"PalAb\">base period</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 41%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">This&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">number</span>&nbsp;can represent</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 1%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">a&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">price</span>,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 1%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">a&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span>,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 1%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">a&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">value in rand</span>,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">or</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 1%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">a&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">number of people</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(11,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The table lists data for the computation of a composite index for the <span class=\"PalBc\">price</span> of food in <span class=\"PalAa\">2009</span>. &nbsp;The <span class=\"PalAb\">base year</span> is <span class=\"PalAb\">2000</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 30%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Item</span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 25%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalBc\">Prices</span> in <span class=\"PalAb\">2000</span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc p_{\\PalAb{2000}}\\)</span></span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 25%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalBc\">Prices</span> in <span class=\"PalAa\">2009</span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc p_{\\PalAa{2009}}\\)</span></span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Simple<br>\r\n		index</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">White bread,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(800\\:\\text{g}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur8\\Cdp50\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 8%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur9\\Cdp75\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 8%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(114\\Ndp71\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 6%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Eggs,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\:\\text{dozen}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur16\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur25\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(156\\Ndp25\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Milk,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\:\\text{litre}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur8\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur11\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(137\\Ndp50\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Granny Smith apples,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\:\\text{kg}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur15\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur19\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(126\\Ndp67\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Orange juice,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\:\\text{litre}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur9\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur12\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(133\\Ndp33\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">100% ground roast coffee,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(500\\:\\text{g}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur51\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur55\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(107\\Ndp84\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span style=\"text-align:center;\">Total</span></span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{\\Cur107\\Cdp50}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{\\Cur131\\Cdp75}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The formula for calculating a <span class=\"PalBc\">composite index</span> is:</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">For a <span class=\"PalBc\">composite price index</span>, substitute the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc n\\)</span> with <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc p\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I_\\PalAa n = \\displaystyle\\frac{\\sum { \\PalBc n_\\PalAa n}}{\\sum { \\PalBc n_\\PalAb0}} \\times 100\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I_\\PalAa n = \\displaystyle\\frac{\\sum { \\PalBc p_\\PalAa n}}{\\sum { \\PalBc p_\\PalAb0}} \\times 100\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The sigma sign signifies a sum. &nbsp;So,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sum \\PalBc p_\\PalAa n\\)</span>&nbsp;is the sum of the <span class=\"PalBc\">prices</span> for the <span class=\"PalAa\">given period</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-