riod?</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top; width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Base</span>-weighted <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> index</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The Laspeyres <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> index</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_L\\left(\\PalAa n \\right) =\\displaystyle \\frac{\\sum{\\PalBc p_\\PalAb 0 \\PalBc q_\\PalAa n}}{\\sum{ \\PalBc p_\\PalAb0\\PalBc q_\\PalAb0 }}\\times 100\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Current</span>-weighted <span class=\"PalBc\">price</span> index</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The Paasche <span class=\"PalBc\">price</span> index</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P_P\\left(\\PalAa n \\right) =\\displaystyle \\frac{\\sum{\\PalBc p_\\PalAa n \\PalBc q_\\PalAa n}}{\\sum{ \\PalBc p_\\PalAb0\\PalBc q_\\PalAa n }}\\times 100\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">How much would a basket of goods consumers buy in the <span class=\"PalAa\">current</span> period, have&nbsp;cost in the <span class=\"PalAb\">base</span> period?</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Current</span>-weighted <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> index</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The Paasche <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> index</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_P\\left(\\PalAa n \\right) =\\displaystyle \\frac{\\sum{\\PalBc p_\\PalAa n \\PalBc q_\\PalAa n}}{\\sum{ \\PalBc p_\\PalAa n\\PalBc q_\\PalAb0 }}\\times 100\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" colspan=\"5\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In all cases:</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc p_\\PalAa n\\)</span></span></span><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&nbsp;is the <span class=\"PalBc\">price</span> in the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa {n^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span> year;<br class=\"BodyText\">\r\n		<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\)</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc p_\\PalAb0\\)</span>&nbsp;is the <span class=\"PalBc\">price</span> in the <span class=\"PalAb\">base</span> year;<br class=\"BodyText\">\r\n		<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc q_\\PalAa n\\)</span>&nbsp;is the <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> in the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa {n^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span> year;<br class=\"BodyText\">\r\n		<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc q_\\PalAb 0\\)</span>&nbsp;is the <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> in the <span class=\"PalAb\">base</span> year.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td rowspan=\"1\" style=\"vertical-align: top; text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(18,'Interpretation','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Interpretation</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">The Laspeyres price index</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The Laspeyres price index for<span class=\"PalAa\"> 2014</span> with <span class=\"PalAb\">2013</span> as the <span class=\"PalAb\">base year</span> is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{98\\Ndp85}\\)</span>. &nbsp;What is the meaning of this?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The index is less than a <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\)</span>. &nbsp;Subtract <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\Ndp00\\)</span> from <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{98\\Ndp85}\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{98\\Ndp85}-100\\Ndp00=-1\\Ndp15\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The result is a negative number, we have a decrease.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the following explanation:&nbsp;You bought a basket of goods in the <span class=\"PalAb\">base</span> period.<br>\r\nIf you bought this basket in the <span class=\"PalAa\">given</span> period, how much would it have cost?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the&nbsp;table below that&nbsp;deals&nbsp;with the prices of magazine advertisement pages.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The first two columns give the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">prices</span>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">2013</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">2014</span>. &nbsp;The last two columns give the number of advertisements placed in&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">2013</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">2014</span>. &nbsp;These last two columns of numbers are called the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">quantities</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0