\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A value index measures changes in both the price and quantities involved.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">A value index</span> is a ratio which indicates how much the value of expenditure has changed as a ratio of expenditure in the base year.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">It gives the value&nbsp;of a basket of goods in a <span class=\"PalAa\">specific year</span> as a percentage of the value of the same basket in the <span class=\"PalAb\">base year</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A value index, such as the index of department store sales, needs the original <span class=\"PalAb\">base year</span> <span class=\"PalBc\">prices</span>, the original <span class=\"PalAb\">base year</span> <span class=\"PalBc\">quantities</span>, the <span class=\"PalAa\">given year </span><span class=\"PalBc\">prices</span> and the <span class=\"PalAa\">given year</span> <span class=\"PalBc\">quantities</span> for its construction.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The formula for the value index is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(V = \\displaystyle\\frac{\\sum \\PalBc p_\\PalAa n \\PalBc q_\\PalAa n}{\\PalBc p_\\PalAb 0\\PalBc q_\\PalAb 0} \\times100\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">where</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc p_\\PalAa n\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the <span class=\"PalBc\">price</span> in the&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{n^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">year</span>,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc q_\\PalAa n\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> in the&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{n^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">year</span>,&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc p_\\PalAb 0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the <span class=\"PalBc\">price</span> in the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">base year</span>,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">and</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc q_\\PalAb 0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the <span class=\"PalBc\">quantity</span> in the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">base year</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(22,'Variables','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Variables</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(23,'Laws of operations','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Laws of operations</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(24,'Activity 1 info','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Activity 1 info</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You are going to watch two videos on the consumer price index. &nbsp;Watch with attention, because afterwards you wi