ine via myUnisa.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Refer to the tutorial letter&nbsp;for more information about the assignment.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;consists of multiple choice questions.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">When you are done, click the &#39;Proceed&#39;\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"{SYSVAR:MEDIA_REL}/653.JPG\" style=\"width: 23px; height: 22px;\">&nbsp;button to<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&nbsp;access the assignment questions.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(57,'Information','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment information</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li>The&nbsp;a<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">ssignment questions following the measures of locality learning unit&nbsp;contribute towards your semester mark and final mark.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">All the assignment questions for&nbsp;the relevant topics can be accessed once all the relevant learning units of the topics have been&nbsp;completed.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;has to be submitted online via myUnisa.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Refer to the tutorial letter&nbsp;for more information about the assignment.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;consists of multiple choice questions.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">When you are done, click the &#39;Proceed&#39;\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"{SYSVAR:MEDIA_REL}/653.JPG\" style=\"width: 23px; height: 22px;\">&nbsp;button to<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&nbsp;access the assignment questions.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(58,'Information','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment information</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li>The&nbsp;a<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">ssignment questions following the measures of dispersion learning unit&nbsp;contribute towards your semester mark and final mark.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">All the assignment questions for&nbsp;the relevant topics can be accessed once all the relevant learning units of the topics have been&nbsp;completed.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;has to be submitted online via myUnisa.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Refer to the tutorial letter&nbsp;for more information about the assignment.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;consists of multiple choice questions.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">When you are done, click the &#39;Proceed&#39; \r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"{SYSVAR:MEDIA_REL}/653.JPG\" style=\"width: 23px; height: 22px;\">&nbsp;button to<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&nbsp;access the assignment questions.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(59,'Order of operations','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Order of operations</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Evaluating mathematical expressions can be a simple process, but needs to follow an order of operations to get the right answer. &nbsp;The following sequence describes&nbsp;the order you follow to add, subtract, multiply&nbsp;and divide. &nbsp;The order is:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">B. E. M. D. A. S</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 33%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Brackets (B)</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Perform the operations inside the brackets first.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Exponents (E)</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Then exponents.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiplication (M)</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Then multiplication, from left to right. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If more than one operation have the same priority, operate from left to right.</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\div\\)</span>&nbsp;have the same priority.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Division (D)</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Then division, from left to right.</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If more than one operation have the same priority, operate from left to right.</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\div\\)</span>&nbsp;have the same priority.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Addition (A)</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Then addition, from left to right.</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If more than one operation have the same priority, operate from left to right.</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(+\\)</span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-\\)</span>&nbsp;have the same priority.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Subtraction (S)</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Then subtraction, from left to right.</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If more than one operation have the same priority, operate from left to right.</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(+\\)</span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-\\)</span>&nbsp;have the same priority.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You can also create a little phrase to memorize&nbsp;the sequence:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Bongi Exercises Most Days After School</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">At school you probably came across:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">B. O. M. D. A. S.</span> or</span> <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">B. O. D. M. A. S.</span> <span class=\"BodyText\">which stands for&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">B</span>rackets,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">O</span>rder (which represents exponents),</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">M</span>ultiplication,&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">D</span>ivision,&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">A</span>ddition and&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">S</span>ubtraction.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This also represents the order of operations.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(60,'Video','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Sometimes it is difficult to simplify a mathematical expression.</span> &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the expression</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 17%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5+2\\times4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">.</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 8%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Is the answer</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 17%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{5+2}\\times4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 8%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{7}\\times4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(28\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">or</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 17%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5+\\PalAb{2\\times4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 8%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5+\\PalAb{8}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\)</span>?</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In mathematics the exact same problem cannot have two or more different answers.<br>\r\nTo eliminate this&nbsp;confusion a common technique for remembering the order of operations, namely&nbsp;BEMDAS&nbsp;was established.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following video will explain this concept. &nbsp;Click on the video to start.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><span class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<video controls=\"\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/327.mp4\" width=\"650\">&nbsp;</video>\r\n</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(61,'With and without','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">With and without brackets</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">Without brackets</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{8-2}+3\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 8%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{6}+3\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(9\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">With brackets</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8-(\\PalAb{2+3})\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8-\\PalAb{5}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In the example <span class=\"PalAa\">without</span> any brackets, the problem is solved by working from <span class=\"PalAa\">left to right</span> and performing all the addition and subtraction.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">When brackets are used, you <span class=\"PalAb\">first </span>perform the operations <span class=\"PalAb\">inside</span> the <span class=\"PalAb\">brackets</span>, so&nbsp;you will get a different answer.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Therefore, if you want a specific order of performing operations you must enforce it using brackets.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(62,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Brackets are used to override preconceived priorities. &nbsp;Brackets are a very powerful means of casting expressions in a form that conveys the specific meaning that we want.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Any expression between brackets is regarded as a number which must be determined first before proceeding further with the calculation. &nbsp;Any expression? &nbsp;Yes.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">But an expression itself may contain brackets. &nbsp;Does this mean that we can have brackets within brackets? &nbsp;Yes, indeed it does. &nbsp;That is, in fact, the beauty and the power of brackets.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Simplify the following expression:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sqrt{(3\\times\\sqrt{(4^2+3^2)}+(4+3)^2)}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Solution</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 4%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 33%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sqrt{(3\\times\\sqrt{(\\PalAa{4^2+3^2})}+(\\PalAb{4+3})^2)}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculate the two sets of innermost brackets&nbsp;first, it does not matter which one first.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 4%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 33%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sqrt{(3\\times\\sqrt{(\\PalAa{16+9})}+\\PalAb{7}^2)}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Within a set of brackets the usual priority&nbsp;rules apply: in the&nbsp;first set, addition after exponentiation.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 4%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 33%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sqrt{(3\\times\\sqrt{\\PalAa{25}}+\\PalAb{7}^2)}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Next do the exponentiation <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\left( \\sqrt{25}=25^{\\frac{1}{2}} \\right)\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7^2\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 4</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 4%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 33%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sqrt{(3\\times5+49)}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiplication <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((3\\times5)\\)</span> is before addition.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 5</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 4%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 33%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sqrt{(15+49)}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Addition.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 6</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 4%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 33%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sqrt{64}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Now we can take the square root.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 7</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 4%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 33%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Result of simplification.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, the simplification of the mathematical expression&nbsp;results in <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(63,'Video 1','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch the first part&nbsp;of this video on&nbsp;the consumer price index:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/349.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(64,'Video 2','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch the second part&nbsp;of this video on&nbsp;the consumer price index:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/350.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:54','2017-10-11 10:04:54','',NULL),(65,'Inflation','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Inflation</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\"