span class=\"PalAa\">smallest</span> number <span class=\"PalAa\">divisible by</span> the <span class=\"PalAa\">denominators</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\)</span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span>, is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{12}\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\displaystyle\\frac{23\\PalAa{\\times3}}{4\\PalAa{\\times3}}+\\displaystyle\\frac{17\\PalAa{\\times2}}{6\\PalAa{\\times2}}-\\displaystyle\\frac{22\\PalAa{\\times4}}{3\\PalAa{\\times4}}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\displaystyle\\frac{69}{\\PalAa{12}}+\\displaystyle\\frac{34}{\\PalAa{12}}-\\displaystyle\\frac{88}{\\PalAa{12}}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Add or subtract the numerators.<br>\r\n		Write the result above the line.<br>\r\n		Keep the <span class=\"PalAa\">lowest common denominator</span> below the line.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\displaystyle\\frac{{69}+{34}-{88}}{\\PalAa{12}}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\displaystyle\\frac{15}{12}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 4</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Simplify</span> the fraction by <span class=\"PalAb\">dividing</span> both the numerator and denominator by the <span class=\"PalAb\">GCF</span>, in this case&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb3\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\displaystyle\\frac{15\\PalAb{\\div3}}{12\\PalAb{\\div3}}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\"