 class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\ell\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(230,'Place value','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Place value</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A very useful diagram which is easy to set up is a stem-and-leaf diagram.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Data can be shown in a variety of ways including graphs, charts and tables. &nbsp;A stem-and-leaf diagram is a type of graph that is similar to a histogram but shows more information. &nbsp;A stem-and-leaf diagram&nbsp;summarises the shape of a set of data (the distribution) and provides extra detail regarding individual values.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The data is arranged by place value. &nbsp;Each data value is split into a <span>leaf</span> (usually the <span>last digit</span>) and a <span>stem</span> (the <span>other digits</span>). &nbsp;The stem values are listed down and the leaf values are listed next to them.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In this way the <span>stem groups the values</span> and each <span>leaf indicates a particular value</span> within the <span>group</span>. &nbsp;The leaves are displayed to the right of the stem. &nbsp;Stem-and-leaf diagrams are great organisers for large amounts of information.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/610.jpg\" style=\"width: 90%; height: 90%;\"></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(231,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The first step in setting up this diagram is to decide how to separate each observation into two parts -&nbsp;the stem and the leaf.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Let us separate Radial&#39;s data in such a way that the first digit of each number is the stem and the second digit is the leaf. &nbsp;We already know that the smallest number is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\)</span> and the largest is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(98\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Thus&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\)</span>&nbsp;has stem <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span>&nbsp;and leaf&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Thus&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(98\\)</span>&nbsp;has stem <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(9\\)</span>&nbsp;and leaf&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">All the other numbers lie between these two and we can therefore set up the stem from <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span> to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(9\\)</span>. &nbsp;Now each number&#39;s second digit is written next to its stem.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Stem</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Leaf</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Frequency</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">1</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">9 6 4</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">3</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">2</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">9 6 2</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">3</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">3</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">8 5 7 4 2</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">5</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">4</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">2 5 6 6 5 5 0</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">7</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">5</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">8 6 9 9 0 9 5 3 1 0 4 8 0 6 8 1 0</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">17</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">6</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">1 6 4 6 4 9 6 6 7 4 4 7 1 1 2 9 2 2 2 7 6</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">21</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">7</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">2 5 7 0 2 8 5 2 5 7 8 0 8 7 0</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">15</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">8</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">8 0 3 2 6 6 0</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">7</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">9</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">8 0</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">2</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(232,'Alt. presentation','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Alt. presentation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Looking at the stem-and-leaf diagram from&nbsp;its&nbsp;side, it is easy to see that most of the customers drove between sixty and seventy thousand kilometres with a set of tyres.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/609.jpg\" style=\"width: 50%; height: 50%;\"></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(233,'Introduction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Introduction</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Often it is not possible to list all the data or draw a histogram. &nbsp;It would be nice to have one number which best represents a data set. &nbsp;Often where the data lies is of interest, for which purpose a measure of location is useful.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">A measure of central tendency is a&nbsp;single value that attempts to describe<br>\r\n		a set of data by identifying&nbsp;the central position within that set of data.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">As such, measures of central tendency are sometimes called measures of central location.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mean (often called the average) is most likely the measure of central tendency that you are most familiar with, but there are others, such as the median and the mode.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Valid measures of central tendency:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Mean</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Median</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Mode</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Under different conditions, some measures of central tendency become more appropriate to use than others.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">It is important to consider&nbsp;the mean, mode and median,&nbsp;how to calculate them and under what conditions they are most appropriate to be used.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(234,'Formula','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Formula</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If we have <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa n\\)</span> values in a data set and they have values <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x_1, x_2,\\ldots,x_\\PalAa n\\)</span>, the <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">sample mean</span>, usually denoted by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\bar{x}\\)</span> (pronounced &quot;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>&nbsp;bar&quot;), is</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\bar{x} = \\displaystyle\\frac{\\left(x_1+x_2+\\ldots+x_\\PalAa n\\right)}{\\PalAa n}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The formula is usually written in a different way:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\bar{x} = \\displaystyle\\frac{\\displaystyle\\sum_{\\PalBc i=1}^{\\PalAa n} x_\\PalBc i}{\\PalAa n}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">where</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\bar{x}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">(read as &quot;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>&nbsp;bar&quot;) is the generally accepted symbol for the arithmetic mean,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa n\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the number<span>&nbsp;</span>of observations,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\sum\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">(pronounced &quot;sigma&quot;) is the Greek letter for S and means &quot;sum of&quot;, and</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x_\\PalBc i\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">represents the&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{ i^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span>&nbsp;observation.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The above formula refers to the sample mean. &nbsp;So, why have we called it a sample mean? &nbsp;This is because, in statistics, samples and populations have very different meanings, which are very important, even if&nbsp;they are calculated in the same way&nbsp;in the case of the mean. &nbsp;We will only consider the sample mean.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You will notice&nbsp;that the mean is not often one of the actual values that you observe&nbsp;in your data set. &nbsp;However, one of its important properties is that it minimises error in the prediction of any one value in your data set.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(235,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mean is the measure of locality used most often. &nbsp;However, sometimes it can be misleading.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the monthly salaries (in <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur1\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\)</span>) of <span class=\"PalAa\">ten</span> staff members at a factory, given&nbsp;below:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table align=\"center\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right; width: 15%;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Staff</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa1\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa2\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa3\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa4\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa6\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa7\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa8\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa9\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{10}\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Salary</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(18\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(16\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(12\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(17\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(90\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(95\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mean is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} \\bar x&amp;=\\displaystyle\\frac{\\left(15+18+16+14+15+15+12+17+90+95\\right)}{\\PalAa{10}}\\\\ &amp;=30\\Ndp70 \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mean salary for these ten staff members is therefore:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur1\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\times30\\Ndp70=\\Cur30\\Tsp700\\Cdp00\\)</span>. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">However, inspecting the data&nbsp;suggests that this mean value of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur30\\Tsp700\\Cdp00\\)</span>&nbsp;<br>\r\nmight not be the best way to accurately reflect the typical&nbsp;salary of a staff member, since&nbsp;most staff members have salaries in the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur12\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\)</span>&nbsp;to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur18\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\)</span>&nbsp;range.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mean is rather sensitive to <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">outliers</span> and may often be misleading. &nbsp;<br>\r\nOutliers are values that are unusual compared to the rest of the data set by being especially small or large in numerical value. &nbsp;On its own, without any additional information, the arithmetic mean may often lead to incorrect conclusions. &nbsp;In this situation, the mean is being skewed by the two large salaries. &nbsp;Therefore, we would like to have a better measure of central tendency. &nbsp;Taking the median would be a better measure of central tendency in this situation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A big advantage of the arithmetic mean is that it uses <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">all</span> the available <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">data</span>. &nbsp;This is not the case for the other measures of locality.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Since the mean can be calculated exactly, it forms the basis for many advanced analyses and is not only descriptive in nature.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(236,'Intervals','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Intervals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Sometimes we are given a chart showing frequencies of certain groups instead of the actual values. &nbsp;We can still come up with a good estimate of a typical value for the set of data, provided that we make some assumptions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">We assume that the values in each interval<br>\r\n		are spread evenly throughout the interval.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If this is the case, then the mean for each interval should be approximately equal to the <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span> for each interval.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;of an interval divides the interval into two equal parts<br>\r\n		and is obtained by&nbsp;</span><span class=\"BodyText\">adding the upper and lower limits of each interval<br>\r\n		and dividing the result by two.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This <span class=\"PalBc\">middle value</span> represents the class interval in calculations.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The tyre company Radial advertised&nbsp;that their&nbsp;<em>XXX</em> tyres will travel at least <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(65\\Tsp000\\)</span> kilometres before one of the four tyres will no longer meet the minimum safety requirements. &nbsp;A frequency table has been drawn up, providing data about intervals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The&nbsp;first interval in Radial&#39;s frequency table is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\Ndp5 - 24\\Ndp5\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span> is found by adding the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">lower interval boundary</span> to the <span class=\"PalAb\">higher interval boundary</span>,&nbsp;<span>then dividing that sum by&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{\\PalAa{13\\Ndp5}+\\PalAb{24\\Ndp5}}{2}\\\\ =\\displaystyle\\frac{38}{2}\\\\ =\\PalBc{19}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span> for the interval <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{13\\Ndp5}-\\PalAb{24\\Ndp5}\\)</span>&nbsp;is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{19}\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(237,'Formula','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Formula</h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The tyre company Radial advertised&nbsp;that their&nbsp;<em>XXX</em> tyres will travel at least&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(65\\Tsp000\\)</span>&nbsp;<br>\r\nkilometres before one of the four tyres will no longer meet the minimum safety requirements. &nbsp;A frequency table has been drawn up, providing data about intervals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoints</span> for the intervals of Radial&#39;s frequency table were&nbsp;calculated, given below. &nbsp;So, for each interval we have the <span class=\"PalAa\">number of values</span>, <span class=\"PalAb\">frequency</span><br>\r\nand a <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Interval</th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Frequency</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb f_\\PalBc i\\)</span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"PalBc\">Midpoint&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x_\\PalBc i\\)</span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Percentage&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\%\\)</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\Ndp5 - 24\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 7%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb4\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 18%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{19}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\Ndp00\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 14%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(24\\Ndp5 - 35\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{30}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\Ndp25\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(35\\Ndp5 - 46\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb9\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{41}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(11\\Ndp25\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(46\\Ndp5 - 57\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{11}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{52}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\Ndp75\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(57\\Ndp5 - 68\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{25}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{63}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(31\\Ndp25\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(68\\Ndp5 - 79\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{17}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{74}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(21\\Ndp25\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(79\\Ndp5 - 90\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb8\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{85}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\Ndp00\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(90\\Ndp5 - 101\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb1\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{96}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp25\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If we multiply each <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span> by its <span class=\"PalAb\">frequency</span>, add them all and then divide by the total <span class=\"PalAa\">number of values</span> in the frequency table, we have an estimate of the mean. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Method to determine&nbsp;estimated mean</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, the method to determine an estimate of the mean is as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 1</span></th>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Determine the <span class=\"PalAa\">total&nbsp;number of values</span> by finding the sum of the <span class=\"PalAb\">frequency</span> values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 10px;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 2</span></th>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiply each <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span> by its <span class=\"PalAb\">frequency</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 3</span></th>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Find the sum of all these products.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 4</span></th>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Divide the sum of these products by the <span class=\"PalAa\">total number of values</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Step 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Determine the <span class=\"PalAa\">total</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">number of values</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} \\PalAa n&amp;= \\sum \\PalAb f_\\PalBc i\\\\ &amp;=\\PalAb4+\\PalAb5+\\PalAb9+\\PalAb{11}+\\PalAb{25}+\\PalAb{17}+\\PalAb8+\\PalAb1\\\\&amp;=\\PalAa{80} \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Step 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiply each <span class=\"PalBc\">midpoint</span> by its <span class=\"PalAb\">frequency</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\">Interval</th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Frequency</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb f_\\PalBc i\\)</span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"PalBc\">Midpoint</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x_\\PalBc i\\)</span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb f_\\PalBc i\\times x_\\PalBc i\\)</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\Ndp5 - 24\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 7%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb 4\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 14%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center; width: 15%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{19}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 18%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{4}\\times\\PalBc{19}=\\)</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 8%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(76\\)</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(24\\Ndp5 - 35\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{30}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{5}\\times\\PalBc{30}=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(150\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(35\\Ndp5 - 46\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb9\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{41}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{9}\\times\\PalBc{41}=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(369\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(46\\Ndp5 - 57\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{11}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{52}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{11}\\times\\PalBc{52}=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(572\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(57\\Ndp5 - 68\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{25}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{63}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{25}\\times\\PalBc{63}=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Tsp575\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(68\\Ndp5 - 79\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{17}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{74}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{17}\\times\\PalBc{74}=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Tsp258\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(79\\Ndp5 - 90\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb8\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{85}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{8}\\times\\PalBc{85}=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(680\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(90\\Ndp5 - 101\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb1\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{96}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{1}\\times\\PalBc{96}=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(96\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Step 3</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Find the sum of&nbsp;the&nbsp;products of the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBc\">midpoints</span>&nbsp;and their&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">frequencies</span>. &nbsp;Add these products together:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} \\sum \\PalAb f_\\PalBc ix_\\PalBc i &amp;=76+150+369+572+1\\Tsp575+1\\Tsp258+680+96\\\\&amp;=4\\Tsp776 \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The sum of the products is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\Tsp776\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Step 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Divide this&nbsp;sum of the&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb f_\\PalBc i\\times x_\\PalBc i\\)</span> products by the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">total number of values</span>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} \\bar{x} &amp;= \\frac{\\displaystyle\\sum \\PalAb f_\\PalBc i x_\\PalBc i}{\\PalAa n}\\\\ &amp;=\\frac{4\\Tsp776}{\\PalAa{80}}\\\\ &amp;=59\\Ndp70 \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Therefore, the estimate of the mean is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(59\\Ndp70\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mean calculated for the raw data (the original <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(80\\)</span> values) of Radial is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(59,79\\)</span>. &nbsp;We did not lose too much information by classifying the data into a frequency table.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You can also use the statistical keys of the SHARP EL-738 calculator to calculate the mean of the data in the frequency table.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Method using SHARP EL-738 calculator</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Make sure that the calculator&nbsp;is set to STAT mode: Press&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\([\\text{MODE}]\\:[\\text{1}]\\:[\\text{0}]\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\([\\text{2ndF}]\\:[\\text{CA}]\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(19\\:[\\text{,}]\\:4\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1.00\\)</span> will be displayed. You have entered the first pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(30\\:[\\text{,}]\\:5\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2.00\\)</span> will be displayed. You have entered the second pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(41\\:[\\text{,}]\\:9\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3.00\\)</span>&nbsp;will be displayed. You have entered the third pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(52\\:[\\text{,}]\\:11\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4.00\\)</span>&nbsp;will be displayed. You have entered the fourth pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(63\\:[\\text{,}]\\:25\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5.00\\)</span>&nbsp;will be displayed. You have entered the fifth pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(74\\:[\\text{,}]\\:17\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6.00\\)</span>&nbsp;will be displayed. You have entered the sixth pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(85\\:[\\text{,}]\\:8\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7.00\\)</span>&nbsp;will be displayed. You have entered the seventh pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(96\\:[\\text{,}]\\:1\\:[\\text{DATA}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8.00\\)</span>&nbsp;will be displayed. You have entered the eighth pair of data values.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\([\\text{ON/C}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\([\\text{RCL}]\\:[\\bar{x}]\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(59.70\\)</span>&nbsp;will be displayed (that is the mean).</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(238,'Definition','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Definition</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mean is sensitive to extreme values and may often lead to misleading conclusions. &nbsp;Therefore,&nbsp;the median is often preferred as a measure of locality.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">The median <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((Me)\\)</span> is the score value which cuts the distribution in half,<br>\r\n		such that half the scores fall above the median and half fall below it.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Computation of the median is relatively straightforward.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We follow two different procedures depending on the number of data values in the sample:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Computing the median of an odd number of data values&nbsp;in the sample</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Computing the median of an even number of data values&nbsp;in the sample</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The first step in both procedures is the same, namely&nbsp;to order the data values from the smallest to largest.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:57','2017-10-11 10:04:57','',NULL),(239,'Example - Odd','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example - Odd</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">When computing the median of an odd number of data values&nbsp;in a&nbsp;sample, the first step is to&nbsp;order the data values from the smallest to largest.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Refer to the example below to discover the rest of the procedure to compute the median of an odd number of data values.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A survey of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span> employees&#39; performance scores out of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\)</span>&nbsp;gave&nbsp;the following&nbsp;results, ordered from lowest to highest:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(32\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(32\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(35\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(36\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(36\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(38\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{38}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(39\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(39\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(39\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(40\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(40\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(45\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(46\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"PalAb\">median</span> is simply the <span class=\"PalAb\">middle number</span>. &nbsp;In the case above the median would be number <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{38}\\)</span>, because&nbsp;there are <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span> scores all together, with <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\)</span> scores to the left and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\)</span> to the right of the median.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">How do we know where the <span class=\"PalAb\">middle number</span> is?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">Given a data set of size <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{n}\\)</span> sorted in ascending sequence,<br>\r\n		the <span class=\"PalBc\">position</span> of the <span class=\"PalAb\">median</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((\\PalAb{Me})\\)</span> is the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{\\left(\\displaystyle\\frac{\\PalAa n+1}{2}\\right)^{\\text{th}}}\\)</span> <span class=\"PalBc\">value</span><span class=\"PalAa\">.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Our data set has&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{15}\\)</span> <span class=\"PalAa\">values</span>, so the <span class=\"PalBc\">position</span> of the <span class=\"PalAb\">median</span> is the following value:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{\\left(\\displaystyle\\frac{\\PalAa n +1}{2}\\right)^{\\text{th