p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number:&nbsp;719268</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date:&nbsp;9 February 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The expression</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(25-(4-2\\times 8)+16 \\div 2 \\times 4\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">can be rewritten as:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(25+12+2\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(25-16+32\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(25+12+32\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(25-12+2\\)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the following equations:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} \\text {A:}&amp;&amp;21-3\\times 2 &amp;= 36\\\\ \\text {B:}&amp;&amp;36\\div3\\times2 &amp;=6 \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Which of the following is true?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only B is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Both A and B are correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Neither A nor B is correct.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number:&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">825579</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 2 August 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(d\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(e\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f\\)</span> represent positive integers. &nbsp;Then according to BEMDAS, in order to simplify<br>\r\nthe expression</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a-b\\times c-((d+c)\\times e-a) \\div f+c\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">first you must calculate:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a-b\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(d+c\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(e-a\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f+c\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the following equations:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} \\text {A:}&amp;&amp;60\\div4+2 &amp;= 10\\\\ \\text {B:}&amp;&amp;32-10+2 &amp;=20 \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Which of the following is true?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only B is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Both A and B are correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Neither A nor B is correct.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(263,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">express relations between numbers in general terms, by making use of symbols or letters</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, an exercise and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(264,'Variables','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Variables</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(265,'Activity 1','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQwNTQ2MTcyNDY1MDMyMiJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-12-15 10:34:37','',NULL),(266,'Activity 2','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQwNTU0NDE5NzE1MDMzMCJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-12-15 10:34:37','',NULL),(267,'Exercise','