to combine??:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: What is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13 \\times 7 + 13 \\times 3\\)</span>?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} 13 \\times 7 + 13 \\times 3 &amp;= 13 \\times (7+3) \\\\ &amp;=13 \\times 10\\\\ &amp;=130 \\end{align} \\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can use it with subtraction too:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Example: What is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(36 \\times 8 -34 \\times 8\\)</span>?</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} 36 \\times 8 -34 \\times 8 &amp;= (36-34) \\times 8 \\\\ \r\n&amp;=2 \\times 8\\\\ &amp;=16 \\end{align} \\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<div>&nbsp;\r\n</div>\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(279,'Activity 2','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQwNjEzNzk1NDE1MDM3MCJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-12-15 10:34:37','',NULL),(280,'Exercise','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Exercise</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(281,'Exercise','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQwNjIwOTU3OTg1MDM3OCJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-12-15 10:34:37','',NULL),(282,'Assignment','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(283,'Questions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Compulsory assignment: Assignment 01, Question 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are registered for the first semester, answer the questions for the first semester.<br class=\"BodyText\">\r\nIf you are registered for the second semester, answer the questions for the second semester.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Assignment 01 is compulsory and you&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">must</span>&nbsp;submit it on&nbsp;<em class=\"BodyText\">my</em>Unisa. &nbsp;The marks will contribute towards&nbsp;your semester mark. &nbsp;You have to obtain the answers for all ten&nbsp;questions of Assignment 01 before you&nbsp;submit Assignment 01 on&nbsp;<em class=\"BodyText\">my</em>Unisa.<br>\r\nTherefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 01 before you can submit it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 719268</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 9 February 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mathematical expression that is NOT equivalent to</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-a(b-c)\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-ab-ac\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a(c-b)\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-(b-c)a\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-ab+ac\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 825579</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 2 August 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mathematical expression that is NOT equivalent to</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(ab(c-d)\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(ba(c-d)\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(cab-dab\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(ab(d-c)\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a(c-d)b\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(284,'Fractions 2','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Fractions 2</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(285,'Learning objectives','<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should be able to:</span></p>\n<ul class=\"BodyText\"><li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">identify&nbsp;a proper fraction, improper fraction, mixed number, equivalent fraction and a reciprocal of a fraction</span></li></ul>\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, exercises and assignment questions.</span></p>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-12-01 11:56:22','',NULL),(286,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">reduce fractions to lowest terms</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">to divide and multiply fractions</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">add and subtract fractions</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">determine&nbsp;the place value in decimal numbers</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">write a decimal number as a fraction</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">write a fraction as a decimal number</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">round numbers</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, videos, exercises and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(287,'Fractions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Fractions</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(288,'Proper fraction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Proper fraction</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(289,'Definition','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Definition of a proper function</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span>When the numerator is less than the denominator,&nbsp;<br>\r\n		we call the expression a proper fraction.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Examples</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}&amp;&amp;\\displaystyle\\frac{2}{3}&amp;&amp;\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{9}&amp;&amp;\\displaystyle\\frac{97}{100}\\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(290,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQwNjQyMDQ1Mzc1MDM4NiJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-12-15 10:34:38','',NULL),(291,'Improper fraction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Improper fraction</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(292,'Definition','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Definition of an improper fraction</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span style=\"color: rgb(70,\r\n 70,\r\n 70); font-family: \'Computer Modern Serif\'; font-size: 18px; line-height: 27px; text-align: center; background-color: rgb(182,\r\n 186,\r\n 186);\">An improper fraction occurs when the numerator<br>\r\n		is&nbsp;greater than or equal to the denominator.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Examples</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align}\\displaystyle\\frac{4}{3}&amp;&amp;\\displaystyle\\frac{19}{7}&amp;&amp;\\displaystyle\\frac{9}{1}&amp;&amp;\\displaystyle\\frac{6}{6}\\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(293,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisa