owards&nbsp;your semester mark. &nbsp;You have to obtain the answers for all ten&nbsp;questions of Assignment 01 before you&nbsp;submit Assignment 01 on&nbsp;<em class=\"BodyText\">my</em>Unisa.<br>\r\nTherefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 01 before you can submit it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 719268</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 9 February 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The expression</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{p}{2r}-\\displaystyle\\frac{q}{rp}+r\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">is the same as:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{p-q+r}{2r-rp}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{p-q+r}{2r-rp+1}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{p^2-2q+2r^2p}{2rp}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{p^2-2q+r}{2rp}\\)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Simplifying</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}+1\\frac{9}{12} \\times 2 \\displaystyle\\frac{1}{7}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">gives:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle 5\\frac{5}{14}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle4\\frac{9}{14}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle 4\\frac{1}{2}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle2\\frac{6}{7}\\)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 825579</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 2 August 2016&nbsp;</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the following equations:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">A: &nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{a}{b} \\div \\displaystyle\\frac{c}{d} = \\displaystyle\\frac{a \\times d}{b \\times c}\\)</span><br>\r\n<br>\r\nB: &nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{a}{b}+\\displaystyle\\frac{c}{d}=\\displaystyle\\frac{a+c}{b+d}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Which of the following is true?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only B is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Both A and B are correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Neither A nor B is correct.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Simplifying</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{2}{3}+2\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{12}\\div 1\\displaystyle\\frac{7}{8}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">gives:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle 1\\displaystyle\\frac{7}{9}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle 1\\displaystyle\\frac{7}{15}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle 1 \\displaystyle\\frac{1}{3}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(329,'Introduction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Introduction</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(330,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">solve problems containing roots</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, videos, exercises and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(331,'Powers','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Powers</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(332,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">solve problems containing powers</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, a video, exercises and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:58','2017-10-11 10:04:58','',NULL),(333,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?lau