bsp;The marks will contribute towards&nbsp;your semester mark. &nbsp;You have to obtain the answers for all ten&nbsp;questions of Assignment 02&nbsp;before you&nbsp;submit Assignment 02&nbsp;on&nbsp;</span><em class=\"BodyText\">my</em><span class=\"BodyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;Therefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 02&nbsp;before you can submit it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 806762</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 23 February 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 3</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The owner of a second hand shop bought an old bookcase for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur1\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\)</span>. &nbsp;He increased the purchase price of&nbsp;the bookcase by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\%\\)</span> to obtain the selling price.<br>\r\nHowever, after <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\)</span> months he had not sold the bookcase&nbsp;and so he reduced the selling price by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span>. &nbsp;When he sold the bookcase he made a percentage profit of:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(35\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(38\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(40\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(45\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Noma found that her car uses <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span> litres of fuel to travel <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\:\\text{km}\\)</span> . &nbsp;If Noma wants to travel <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\:\\text{km}\\)</span> &nbsp;then the&nbsp;number of litres of fuel that the car will use is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{x}{yz}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{yz}{x}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{y}{xz}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{xz}{y}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A manufacturer&nbsp;uses three main ingredients to make polish. &nbsp;These ingredients are melted wax, water&nbsp;and white spirits and they are used in the ratio of</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}:1\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{2}:\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{4}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">How many litres of each ingredient must be used to make <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(70\\)</span> litres of polish?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(30\\)</span> litres of melted wax, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(30\\)</span> litres of water and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\)</span> litres of white spirits</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\)</span> litres of melted wax, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(48\\)</span> litres of water and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8\\)</span> litres of white spirits</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(21\\)</span> litres of melted wax, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(42\\)</span> litres of water and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\)</span> litres of white spirits</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\)</span> litres of melted wax, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(40\\)</span> litres of water and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\)</span> litres of white spirits</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 733287</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 16 August 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 3</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Susan bought a microwave oven for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur999\\Cdp95\\)</span> including VAT. &nbsp;The rate of VAT is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\%\\)</span>. &nbsp;The price of the&nbsp;microwave excluding VAT, to the nearest cent, is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur799\\Cdp95\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur859\\Cdp96\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur877\\Cdp15\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur1\\Tsp139\\Cdp94\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Noma found that her car uses&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>&nbsp;litres of fuel to travel&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\:\\text{km}\\)</span>&nbsp;. &nbsp;The distance, in <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{km}\\)</span>, that she can travel&nbsp;using <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\)</span> litres of fuel is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{x}{yz}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{yz}{x}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{y}{xz}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{xz}{y}\\)</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A piece of timber is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\:\\text{cm}\\)</span> long. &nbsp;It is cut into two pieces A and B, the lengths of which are in the ratio&nbsp;of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3:7\\)</span>, respectively. &nbsp;The piece B is then cut into two pieces C and D, the lengths of which are in the&nbsp;ratio of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5:9\\)</span>, respectively. &nbsp;The lengths of A, C and D, respectively are in the ratio of:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3:5:9\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3:7:9\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6:5:9\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6:7:9\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:59','2017-10-11 10:04:59','',NULL),(389,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should know and be able to use:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">all the basic signs and notations</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">the counting rules</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, videos, an exercise and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:59','2017-10-11