ill contribute towards&nbsp;your semester mark. &nbsp;You have to obtain the answers for all ten&nbsp;questions of Assignment 02&nbsp;before you&nbsp;submit Assignment 02&nbsp;on&nbsp;<em class=\"BodyText\">my</em>Unisa. &nbsp;Therefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 02&nbsp;before you can submit it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number:&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">806762</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 23 February 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The inequality that is INCORRECT is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-11&lt;-13\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8&gt;-4\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-2&lt;3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">None of the above</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the following equations:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">A: &nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(_8P_3={_8P_5}\\)</span><br>\r\nB: &nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(_8C_3={_8C_5}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Which of the following is true?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Neither A nor B is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Both A and B are correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only B is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A is correct.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The sum</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\sum^{5}_{i=1}i^2\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">is equal to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(225\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(144\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(55\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 733287</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 16 August 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(p\\)</span> is a real number. &nbsp;Consider the following statements:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">A: &nbsp;If <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(p\\leq0\\)</span>, then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-4p\\leq0\\)</span>.<br>\r\nB: &nbsp;On a number line, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(p\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-p\\)</span> are the same distance away from <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(0\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Which of the following is true?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only B is correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Both A and B are correct.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Neither A nor B is correct.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A fruit vendor has to pick any five types of fruit from the market. &nbsp;The market has the following types of<br>\r\nfruit in stock:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">apples; bananas; mangoes; oranges; peaches; strawberries; pears; grapes</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The number of choices he can make is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(56\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(336\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\Tsp720\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8^5\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The expression</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x^2_1f(x_1)+x^2_2f(x_2)+x^2_3f(x_3)+x^2_4f(x_4)+x^2_5f(x_5)\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">can be written in summation notation as:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\sum^{5}_{i=1}x^2f(x)\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\sum^{5}_{i=1}x^if(x_i)\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\sum^{5}_{i=1}x^2_1f(x_1)\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\sum^{5}_{i=1}x^2_if(x_i)\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:59','2017-10-11 10:04:59','',N