ing2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number:&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">806762</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 23 February 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 9</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Simplifying the ratio of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\:\\text{m}\\)</span> to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(250\\:\\text{mm}\\)</span> to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\:\\text{cm}\\)</span> gives:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(40:5:1\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8:1:2\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4:5:1\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1:125:25\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 10</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A builder needs to lay a concrete path around the outside of an <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(18\\:\\text{m}\\)</span> by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\:\\text{m}\\)</span> rectangular area of grass. &nbsp;If the width of the path must be <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\:\\text{m}\\)</span> and the concrete must have a depth of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\:\\text{cm}\\)</span>, then the amount of&nbsp;concrete that the builder needs, correct to one decimal place, is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\Ndp4\\:\\text{m}^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\Ndp0\\:\\text{m}^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(74\\Ndp0\\:\\text{m}^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(70\\Ndp0\\:\\text{m}^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 733287</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 16 August 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 9</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Mr Malaka makes a scale drawing of his office. The enlarged representation is shown below:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"160\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/493.JPG\" width=\"350\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On the drawing <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\frac{1}{2}\\:\\text{cm}\\)</span> represents an actual length of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\:\\text{m}\\)</span>. &nbsp;He wishes to tile his office with square tiles. &nbsp;The&nbsp;length of a tile is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(25\\:\\text{cm}\\)</span>. &nbsp;The minimum number of tiles that is required is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\times16\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\times16\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(22\\times16\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(28\\times16\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 10</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A cube of lead, where each side has a length of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(0\\Ndp075\\:\\text{m}\\)</span>, is melted. &nbsp;The molten lead is then poured into&nbsp;a rectangular tin with length <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(12\\Ndp5\\:\\text{cm}\\)</span> and width <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\:\\text{cm}\\)</span>. &nbsp;The tin is then completely full. &nbsp;The height of the&nbsp;tin in millimetres is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\Ndp625\\times10\\)</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\Ndp625\\times10^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\Ndp625\\times10^{-5}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\Ndp625\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:59','2017-10-11 10:04:59','',NULL),(421,'Transformation and rates','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Transformation and rates</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:59','2017-10-11 10:04:59','',NULL),(422,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">calculate quantity indexes</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">calculate value indexes</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">calculate price indexes</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">calculate the consumer price index</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, videos, exercises and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:04:59','2017-10-11 10:04:59','',NULL),(423,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should be able to:</span><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\" class=\"BodyText\">?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">calculate the purchasing power in a specific period</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">calculate an exchange rate</span