stions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment 03, Questions 5, 6, 7&nbsp;and 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If you are registered for the first semester, answer the questions for the first semester.</span><br class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<span class=\"BodyText\">If you are registered for the second semester, answer the questions for the second semester.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Submit Assignment 03&nbsp;on&nbsp;</span><em class=\"BodyText\">my</em><span class=\"BodyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;The marks will contribute towards&nbsp;your semester mark. &nbsp;You have to obtain the answers for all eight&nbsp;questions of Assignment 03&nbsp;before you&nbsp;submit Assignment 03&nbsp;on&nbsp;</span><em class=\"BodyText\">my</em><span class=\"BodyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;Therefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 03&nbsp;before you can submit it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number:&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">677160</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 8 March 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Questions 5 and 6 are based on the following information:<br>\r\nThe following table gives the annual real GDP of a country for the years 2009 to 2013:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 30%;\">Year</th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\">Real annual GDP</th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Computer Modern Serif\'; font-size: 18px; line-height: 27px; text-align: center;\">(All figures in&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\Tsp000\\)</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Computer Modern Serif\'; font-size: 18px; line-height: 27px; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;units of currency)</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2009</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\Tsp418\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2010</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\Tsp779\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2011</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\Tsp052\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2012</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\Tsp471\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2013</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\Tsp685\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The annual real growth rate per year from 2009 to 2012, rounded to two decimal places, is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp78\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\Ndp13\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\Ndp38\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\Ndp30\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose the annual real growth rate from 2010 to 2014 is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\Ndp34\\%\\)</span>. &nbsp;Then the real annual GDP for 2014, in&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\Tsp000\\)</span> units of currency, rounded to the nearest integer, is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\Tsp865\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(16\\Tsp212\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\Tsp485\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(16\\Tsp186\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A woman&rsquo;s salary for the years 2009, 2011 and 2013 as well as the CPI for these years are given in the&nbsp;table below. &nbsp;The base year is 2009 with a CPI of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 25%;\">Year</th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\">Yearly salary in rands</th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 25%;\">CPI</th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2009</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(159\\Tsp820\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2011</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(171\\Tsp850\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(99\\Ndp7\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2013</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(182\\Tsp820\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(102\\Ndp1\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider the statements below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">A: The difference between her nominal salary of 2011 and 2009 is less than the difference between her&nbsp;real salary of 2011 and 2009.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nB: The difference between her nominal salary of 2011 and 2009 is greater than the difference between&nbsp;her real salary of 2011 and 2009.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nC: The difference between her nominal salary of 2013 and 2009 is less than the difference between her&nbsp;real salary of 2013 and 2009.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Which of the following is true?</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only B.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only C.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only B and C.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Jennifer went on holiday to England during April 2014. &nbsp;Before leaving South Africa she purchased <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(470\\)</span>&nbsp;pounds (&pound;) at an exchange rate of</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span>&pound; <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\Cur17\\Cdp64\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On her return she exchanged the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(80\\)</span> pounds which she had not spent, back to rands at an exchange rate&nbsp;of</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\)</span>&pound; = <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur101\\Cdp28\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thus, on the two transactions, not taking into account any other costs incurred, she:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">made a profit of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur188\\Cdp40\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">made a profit of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur60\\Cdp80\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">made a loss of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur188\\Cdp40\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">made a loss of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur60\\Cdp80\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number: 646578</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 30 August 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sipho earned <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur160\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\)</span> in 2012 and received a <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\Ndp5\\%\\)</span> increase in 2013. &nbsp;The CPI (consumer price index) in&nbsp;2013 was&nbsp;computed as <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(103\\Ndp2\\)</span> using 2012 as the base year with a CPI of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\)</span>. &nbsp;Taking the CPI into account,&nbsp;Sipho&rsquo;s inflation adjusted salary in 2013, rounded to the nearest rand, was:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur175\\Tsp504\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur166\\Tsp667\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur165\\Tsp120\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur155\\Tsp039\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>On 20 July 2015 the gold price dropped to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\($1\\Tsp112\\Cdp61\\)</span> per fine ounce and the exchange rate was then</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\($15\\Cdp00=\\Cur186\\Cdp50\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(32\\Ndp15\\)</span> fine ounces in one kilogram of gold. &nbsp;The value of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(125\\:\\text{g}\\)</span> of gold, in rands, was then:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\Tsp557\\Ndp96\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(23\\Tsp015\\Ndp81\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(53\\Tsp784\\Ndp80\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(55\\Tsp593\\Ndp18\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose the annualised quarterly GDP for the second quarter of 2014 was <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span> rands and that for the third&nbsp;quarter was <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span> rands. &nbsp;Suppose the seasonally adjusted and annualised quarterly (Q/Q) growth rate from&nbsp;the second quarter to the third quarter of 2014 was <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp96\\%\\)</span>. &nbsp;After substituting the values into the formula&nbsp;for calculating the (Q/Q) growth rate and manipulating the formula, the correct option is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{x}{y}=\\left(1+\\frac{1\\Ndp96}{100} \\right)^4\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{y}{x}=(1+1\\Ndp96\\times100)^4\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{x}{y}=(1+0\\Ndp0196)^{\\frac{1}{4}}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{y}{x}=(1+0\\Ndp0196)^{\\frac{1}{4}}\\)</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>If the annual growth rate of a certain country for the years from 2010 to 2014 is negative, then:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{GDP}_{2010}&lt;\\text{GDP}_{2014}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{GDP}_{2010}&gt;\\text{GDP}_{2014}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{GDP}_{2010}=\\text{GDP}_{2014}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">the relationship between <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{GDP}_{2010}\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{GDP}_{2014}\\)</span> cannot be determined.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(458,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should know and be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">explain what a sample and a population are</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">explain what simple random sampling, stratified random sampling and systematic sampling are</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, videos, an exercise and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(459,'Introduction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Introduction</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(460,'Sampling','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Sampling</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(461,'Simple random sampling','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Simple random sampling</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(462,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ3MDA1NzIxNTExNzk1OTQ3NSJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100