odyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp61\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 20%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Mark</span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">Male</span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp78\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 3</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Divide the employees by gender into two strata. &nbsp;A stratified random sample of eight employees must be&nbsp;selected. &nbsp;Therefore, the number of female employees in the sample is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The employees are numbered from 1 to 20. The following random numbers are available for sampling<br>\r\npurposes:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(09;\\:40;\\:15;\\: 18;\\: 03;\\: 12;\\: 55;\\: 09;\\: 37;\\: 32;\\: 70;\\: 20;\\: 13;\\: 44;\\: 62;\\: 16\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">These numbers are used to draw a simple random sample of eight employees from the agency. &nbsp;The&nbsp;following employees are included in the random sample:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Kim; Paul; Liza; Jane; Sipho; Kim; Mark; Mirriam</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Kim; Chris; Paul; Liza; Jane; Sipho; Julie; Jill</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Kim; Paul; Liza; Jane; Sipho; Mark; Mirriam; Richard</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Alan; Steve; Jane; Chris; Julie; Stuart; Jill; John</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Second semester</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Unique number: 677857</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Due date: 13 September 2016</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Question 1</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A street has <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span> houses with the following house and stand numbers:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 20%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">House number</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(9\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(11\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(12\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 15%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Stand number</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(230\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(229\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(228\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(227\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(226\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(225\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(224\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(223\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(222\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(221\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(220\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(219\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(218\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(217\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(216\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following random numbers are available for sampling purposes:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5220;\\:7803;\\:3214;\\:1008;\\:4817;\\:4612\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The house numbers only have two digits, that is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span> to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(15\\)</span>. &nbsp;Therefore, select the last two digits of the given&nbsp;random numbers. &nbsp;Draw a simple random sample of four houses according to the house numbers. &nbsp;The&nbsp;stand numbers relating to this random sample are:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3;\\: 14;\\: 08;\\: 12\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(220;\\: 228;\\: 217;\\: 223\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(230;\\: 226;\\: 222;\\: 218\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(228;\\: 217;\\: 223;\\: 219\\)</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Question 2</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In general, the best sample is one that is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">a systematic sample.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">representative of the population.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">convenient.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">purposefully selected.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Question 3</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A researcher divides the population of product users into three groups based on degree of use. &nbsp;If the&nbsp;researcher then draws a simple random sample from each user group independently, she has created a:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">simple random sample.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">stratified random sample.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">group data sample.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">systematic sample.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Question 4</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Sipho Galane, a concerned citizen, has decided to conduct a study of the voters in his town to determine&nbsp;if they approve of the way the mayor is running the council. &nbsp;He intends to ask <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(300\\)</span> citizens of voting&nbsp;age their views in order to obtain an approval rating (a percentage) that will be published in the local&nbsp;newspaper. &nbsp;Sipho comes from a large town. &nbsp;The town clerk, who monitors the voting booths, informed&nbsp;him that all the voters in the entire town registered at a recent election and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(310\\Tsp000\\)</span> voters were counted. &nbsp;Consider the following statements:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">A: &nbsp;The <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(310\\Tsp000\\)</span> registered voters in the town form the population.<br>\r\nB: &nbsp;The sample unit is the vote of a particular citizen.<br>\r\nC: &nbsp;The group of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(300\\)</span> citizens that Sipho Galane will interview form the sample.<br>\r\nD: &nbsp;The variable that will be studied, is a particular citizen.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Which of the following is true?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A, B and C</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A, B and D</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A and C</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only C</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(470,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should know and be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">distinguish between qualitative and quantitative data</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">draw up and interpret a frequency table</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">draw and interpret a histogram</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">draw and interpret a pie chart</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">draw and interpret a cumulative frequency polygon</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">draw and interpret a stem-and-leaf diagram</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, videos, an exercise and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(471,'Introduction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Introduction</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(472,'Activity 1','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQxODkwOTMzNTc1MTE4NiJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-12-15 10:34:44','',NULL),(473,'Activity 2','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQxODk3MzM3MTM1MTE5NiJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-12-15 10:34:44','',NULL),(474,'Bar representations','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Bar representations</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2