style=\"width: 8%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">D:</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">This graph is called an ogive graph.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Which of the following is true?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A, B and C</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A, B and D</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only C and D</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only C</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the frequency table provided above. &nbsp;The percentage of the month that less than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(80\\)</span>&nbsp;motorists called&nbsp;in per day, rounded to two decimal places, is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\Ndp00\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\Ndp00\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\Ndp50\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(19\\Ndp35\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following pie chart shows the percentage distribution on the expenditure incurred in publishing a&nbsp;book.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"280\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/495.JPG\" width=\"310\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If for a certain quantity of books, the publisher has to pay <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur30\\Tsp600\\Cdp00\\)</span> for printing costs, then the amount&nbsp;to be paid for the paper of these books is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur48\\Tsp960\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur73\\Tsp440\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur76\\Tsp500\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur122\\Tsp400\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The stem-and-leaf diagram below shows the distribution of the number of minutes that it takes a group&nbsp;of workers at a factory to get to work each day&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\((3\\:|3=33\\:\\text{minutes})\\)</span>&nbsp;as reported in a survey.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"200\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/496.JPG\" width=\"230\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The statement that is NOT&nbsp;true is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The worker who takes the longest to get to work, takes <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\:\\text{minutes}\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">There are five workers who take less than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(30\\:\\text{minutes}\\)</span> to get to work.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">There are <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\)</span> workers involved in this survey.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">There are four workers who take more than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(40\\:\\text{minutes}\\)</span> to get to work.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(496,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should know and be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">calculate the mean, the mode and the median of a data set</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\