e\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODQyMTA5MzI4Nzc1MTUzNiJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-12-15 10:34:47','',NULL),(527,'Exercise','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Exercise</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(528,'Exercise','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ3MDA1ODU2ODQ0MzY1OTU1NSJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-12-15 10:34:47','',NULL),(529,'Assignment','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(530,'Questions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment 05, Questions 5, 6, 7 and 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If you are registered for the first semester, answer the questions for the first semester.</span><br class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<span class=\"BodyText\">If you are registered for the second semester, answer the questions for the second semester.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Submit Assignment 05&nbsp;on&nbsp;</span><em class=\"BodyText\">my</em><span class=\"BodyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;The marks will contribute towards&nbsp;your semester mark. &nbsp;You have to obtain the answers for all eight&nbsp;questions of Assignment 05&nbsp;before you&nbsp;submit Assignment 05&nbsp;on&nbsp;</span><em class=\"BodyText\">my</em><span class=\"BodyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;Therefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 05&nbsp;before you can submit it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Unique number: 781888</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Due date: 12 April 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Questions 5, 6 and 7 are based on the following information:<br>\r\nThe number of days sick leave taken by the employees of a large company was recorded for the year 2013. &nbsp;The data are summarised in the following diagram.</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"400\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/619.JPG\" width=\"340\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider the period January to June 2013. &nbsp;The first, second and third quartile of the data are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_1=32,\\:Q_2=55\\text{ and }Q_3=65\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_1=12,\\:Q_2=55\\text{ and }Q_3=95\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_1=36,\\:Q_2=49\\text{ and }Q_3=62\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_1=12,\\:Q_2=32\\text{ and }Q_3=55\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider the period July to December 2013 in the box-and-whiskers diagram given above. &nbsp;The&nbsp;quartile deviation, rounded to two decimal places, is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(33\\Ndp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(16\\Ndp50\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\Ndp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(49\\Ndp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider the box-and-whiskers diagram given above. &nbsp;The correct statement is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">On the day in 2013 on which the minimum number of people took sick leave, twelve people were&nbsp;<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">sick.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">During the period January to June, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\%\\)</span> of the time more than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(49\\)</span> people were sick on a particular&nbsp;<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">day.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">During the period January to June, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(75\\%\\)</span> of the time more than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(32\\)</span> people were sick on a particular&nbsp;<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">day.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">During the period July to December, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(25\\%\\)</span> of the time fewer than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(32\\)</span> people were sick on a particular&nbsp;<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">day.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>From 2004 to 2010 the winning scores for a golf tournament were</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(276,\\:278,\\:285,\\:280,\\:277,\\:282\\text{ and }268\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mean winning score is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(278\\)</span>. &nbsp;When calculating the variance of the winning scores</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S^2=\\displaystyle\\frac{\\displaystyle\\sum_{i=1}^{7}(x_i-\\bar{x})^2}{n-1}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>the quantity</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\sum_{i=1}^{7}(x_i-\\bar{x})^2\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>is equal to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Tsp946\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(174\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(0\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(29\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Second semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: left;\">Unique number: 797663</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: right;\">Due date: 27 September 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A company investigates the lengths of international business phone calls of a number of their employees. &nbsp;The table below displays the results of the survey:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Time in minutes</span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Number of employees</span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Midpoint</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Interval limits</span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Frequency&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\((f)\\)</span></span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\((x)\\)</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\Ndp5-11\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(8\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(11\\Ndp5-17\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(11\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(17\\Ndp5-23\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(19\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(23\\Ndp5-29\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(12\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(26\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(29\\Ndp5-35\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(32\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>The mean length of international business phone calls is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(21\\Ndp21\\)</span> minutes. &nbsp;The standard deviation of international business phone calls, rounded to one decimal place, is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(9\\Ndp5\\text{ minutes}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\Ndp5\\text{ minutes}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\Ndp4\\text{ minutes}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\Ndp4\\text{ minutes}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Two motor salesmen have obtained the following statistics on their sales of motor vehicles:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\">Salesman</th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Mean number of sales</span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Variance of sales</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">A</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(300\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(400\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">B</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(280\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(625\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Considering the coefficient of variation <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((CV)\\)</span>, the salesman who is more consistent in his sales, is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">salesman A.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(CV_\\text{A}=CV_\\text{B}\\)</span> which means they are equally consistent.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">no one, because the results are inconclusive.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">salesman B.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 7</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Molly achieved a score of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(950\\)</span> on a national achievement test. &nbsp;The mean test score was <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(850\\)</span> with a standard&nbsp;deviation of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\)</span>. &nbsp;Assume that the test scores are normally distributed. &nbsp;The percentage students that had&nbsp;a higher score than Molly is approximately:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(16\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(32\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(34\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(68\\%\\)</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 8</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider the following box-and-whiskers diagram:</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"150\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1501/assets/620.JPG\" width=\"610\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider the following statements:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 40px;\">A: The distribution is negatively skewed.<br>\r\nB: The difference between <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_3\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(Q_1\\)</span> is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span>.<br>\r\nC: The median is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13\\)</span>.<br>\r\nD: The range of the data is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Which of the following is true?</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only C</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only C and D</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A, B and C</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Only A, C and D</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 10:05:00','2017-10-11 10:05:00','',NULL),(531,'add_topic','\r\n<form action=\"topics_add.php\" method=\"post\">Topic: <input name=\"topic_name\" type=\"text\"><br>\r\nOrder: <input name=\"ordering\" type=\"text\"><br>\r\n<input 