proceed to&nbsp;the next&nbsp;learning unit.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(578,'Information','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment information</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The&nbsp;a<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">ssignment questions following the amortisation learning unit&nbsp;contribute towards your semester mark and final mark.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">All the assignment questions for&nbsp;the relevant topics can be accessed once all the relevant learning units of the topics have been&nbsp;completed.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;has to be submitted online via myUnisa.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Refer to the tutorial letter&nbsp;for more information about the assignment.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;consists of multiple choice questions. </span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"BodyText\">Click&nbsp;the &#39;Continue&#39;&nbsp;button to</span><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&nbsp;access the assignment questions following&nbsp;the amortisation learning unit.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(579,'Definition','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Definitions</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">An annuity is a sequence of equal payments at equal intervals of time.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"430\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/88.html\" width=\"650\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Payments</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Equal&nbsp;cash flows&nbsp;one period apart</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Payment interval/Period</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Time between successive&nbsp;payments</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"PalAb\">Term</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Time from beginning of first&nbsp;payment interval to end of last payment interval</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><br>\r\n<span class=\"PalAa\">Examples of annuities</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Student loan payments</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Car loan payments</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Insurance premiums</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Mortgage payments</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Retirement savings</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(580,'Ordinary annuity and annuity due','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Ordinary annuity and annuity due</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Ordinary annuity</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">An annuity is termed an <span class=\"PalAa\">ordinary annuity</span> when payments are&nbsp;<br>\r\n		made&nbsp;at the&nbsp;same time that interest is credited, that is&nbsp;at the&nbsp;</span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"PalAa\">end</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;of&nbsp;the payment intervals.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"420\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/89.html\" width=\"650\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Annuity due</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">By contrast, an annuity whose periodic payment is made at the&nbsp;</span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"PalAb\">beginning</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;of each payment interval is known as an <span class=\"PalAb\">annuity due</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"420\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/90.html\" width=\"650\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(581,'Annuity certain and perpetuity','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Annuity certain and perpetuity</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Annuity certain</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">If the payments begin and end on&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">fixed dates</span><span class=\"BodyText\">,<br>\r\n		the annuity&nbsp;is known as an <span class=\"PalAa\">annuity certain</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"420\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/91.html\" width=\"650\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Perpetuity</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">On the other hand, if the payments continue&nbsp;</span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"PalAb\">forever</span><span class=\"BodyText\">, the&nbsp;annuity is known as <span class=\"PalAb\">perpetuity</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"420\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/92.html\" width=\"650\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(582,'Examples','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Examples of annuities</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The basic concepts of annuities are illustrated by the following examples. &nbsp;Notice how timelines, with the interest period as the unit, are used.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The premium on an endowment policy is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 2 \\Tsp 400 \\Cdp 00\\)</span> per year, payable for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\)</span> years&nbsp;and payable at the end of each period.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"340\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/93.html\" width=\"650\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Here the payment interval is one year and the term is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\)</span> years. &nbsp;Since the payments are made at the end of each period, this is an <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">ordinary annuity certain</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit focuses on the ordinary annuity certain. &nbsp;When simply referring to an annuity,&nbsp;unless stated otherwise,&nbsp;it&nbsp;means an ordinary annuity certain.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The monthly rent for a shop is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 1 \\Tsp 000 \\Cdp 00\\)</span>&nbsp;payable in advance.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"340\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/94.html\" width=\"650\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Here&nbsp;the payment interval is one month&nbsp;while the term will be determined by the contract. &nbsp;Since the payment is made at the beginning of each period, this is an <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">annuity due</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example 3</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A company is expected to pay <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 180 \\Cdp 00\\)</span>&nbsp;indefinitely&nbsp;every six months&nbsp;on a share of its preferred stock.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This is an example of <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">perpetuity</span> with payment interval of six months. In this case, no term is defined, since payments continue indefinitely.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">In this learning unit we shall concentrate mainly on the ordinary annuity certain.<br>\r\nFrom now on, we shall simply speak of &ldquo;an annuity&rdquo;, and, unless otherwise stated,<br>\r\nwill mean an ordinary annuity certain.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(583,'Video','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch this video on calculating the future value of an annuity:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/82.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(584,'Formula','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">A formula for calculating the future value of annuity</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We have seen that if <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span> is the payment in rand made at each payment interval in respect of an annuity at interest rate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> per payment interval, then the amount or future value of the annuity after <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> intervals is given by the formula:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 29%;\">where</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 61%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the future value of the annuity</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the regular payment</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the interest rate per payment interval</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the number of payment intervals</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(585,'Calculate S and R','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Calculate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Definition\">Four variables are needed when determining the&nbsp;future&nbsp;value&nbsp;of an annuity, namely&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span>. &nbsp;If you know any three of these variables, the fourth can be determined.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following two types of calculations are relevant:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"PalAa\">Calculate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span> when <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> are known</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"PalAb\">Calculate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span> when <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> are known</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculate&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;when&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;are known</span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Use the formula for the future value of an annuity:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 29%; text-align: right;\">where</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 61%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the future value of the annuity</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the regular payment</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the interest rate per payment interval</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the number of payment intervals</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"PalAb\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculate&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;when&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;are known</span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Manipulate the formula for the future value of an annuity to solve for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 35%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Future value of annuity</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\times\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Multiply both sides</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S \\times\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{i}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right] \\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\times\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right] \\times\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{i}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right] \\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span>&nbsp;alone&nbsp;</span><span>on right</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S \\times\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{i}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right]\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span>&nbsp;on left</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S \\times\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{i}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right]\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Simplify</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: middle;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S \\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{i}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right]\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(586,'Video','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch this video on calculating the present value of an annuity:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/83.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(587,'Formula','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">A formula for calculating the present value of annuity</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We have seen that if <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span> is the payment in rand made at each payment interval in respect of an annuity at interest rate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> per payment interval, then the present value of the annuity after <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> intervals is given by the formula:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P=R\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\">where</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 65%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the present value of the annuity</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the regular payment</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the interest rate per payment interval</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the number of payment intervals</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(588,'Calculate P and R','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Calculate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Four variables are needed when determining the present&nbsp;value&nbsp;of an annuity, namely&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">. &nbsp;If you know any three of these variables, the fourth can be determined.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following two types of calculations are relevant:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"PalAa\">Calculate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span> when <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> are known</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"PalAb\">Calculate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span> when <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> are known</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculate&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;when&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;are known</span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Use the formula for the present value of an annuity:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P=R\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 25%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">where</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 65%;\">is the present value&nbsp;of the annuity</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td>is the regular payment</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td>is the interest rate per payment interval</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td>is the number of payment intervals</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><span class=\"PalAb\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculate&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;when&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">,&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;are known</span></span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Manipulate the formula for the present value of an annuity to solve for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 35%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Present value of annuity</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\times\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 35%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiply both sides</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P \\times\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{i(1+i)^n}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right] \\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\times\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\times\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{i(1+i)^n}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right] \\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 35%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>&nbsp;alone on right</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P \\times\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{i(1+i)^n}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right] \\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 35%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>&nbsp;on left</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P \\times\\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{i(1+i)^n}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right] \\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 35%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Simplify</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; vertical-align: middle; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: middle; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P \\left[[\\displaystyle\\frac{i(1+i)^n}{(1+i)^n-1}\\right] \\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(589,'Specific cases','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">The relationship between <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span>: Specific cases</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">How do you&nbsp;distinguish between the present and future value of an annuity?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Future value</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculating the future value of an annuity allows you to see what<br>\r\n		the value will be of the sum of individual amounts in the future.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose you want a lump sum of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 1000 \\Tsp 000 \\Cdp 00 \\)</span> in <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(50\\)</span> years, the future value calculation will tell you how much you need to save each month at a given interest rate. &nbsp;In other words, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 1000 \\Tsp 000 \\Cdp 00\\)</span> is the future value of your regular monthly investment.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Present value</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">As an annuity is a series of equal payments or receipts, the present value<br>\r\n		of an annuity is the sum of the present values of the individual amounts.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If you can afford a mortgage repayment of a certain amount per month, calculating the present value of the repayments at a fixed rate of interest over a given number of years, will tell you the principal sum you can afford to borrow.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, suppose you can afford a monthly&nbsp;payment of&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 3 \\Tsp 000 \\Cdp 00 \\)</span>&nbsp;on a&nbsp;loan to buy a car,&nbsp;taken out on 30 May 2012 for&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(48\\)</span>&nbsp;months beginning on 30 June 2012 at an&nbsp;interest rate of&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(14\\%\\)</span>&nbsp;per&nbsp;annum&nbsp;compounded&nbsp;monthly. &nbsp;If you now calculate the price of the car, this would be the principal sum you can afford to borrow.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The present value is also the amount of money you&nbsp;need&nbsp;to invest now<br>\r\n		in order to&nbsp;withdraw a&nbsp;certain&nbsp;amount&nbsp;of money for a specified period<br>\r\n		of time in the future.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose you invested a&nbsp;certain amount on 1 January 2010 in such a way that it generated a periodic payment of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 1 \\Tsp 500 \\Cdp 00\\)</span> at the end of each month of the calendar year 2010 at an&nbsp;interest rate of&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(13 \\Ndp 2\\% \\)</span> per year, compounded monthly. &nbsp;If you now calculate the original investment, this would be the amount you needed to invest.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(590,'Relationship between formulas','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">The relationship between formulas</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Present value of annuity</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Future value of annuity</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\"><br>\r\n		<span class=\"BodyText\">where</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: center;\"><br>\r\n		<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 65%; text-align: left;\"><br>\r\n		<span class=\"BodyText\"><span>is the present value of the annuity</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 65%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>is the future value of the annuity</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 65%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the regular payment</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 65%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the interest rate per payment interval</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 25%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span><br>\r\n		&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 65%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the number of payment intervals</span><br>\r\n		&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align: center; width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Relationship between present and future values of annuity</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 45%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}=\\PalAb{S}\\div(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p>and</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}=\\PalAa{P}\\times(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><br>\r\n<span class=\"BodyText\">This&nbsp;relationship between the present and future values of an annuity can be&nbsp;illustrated as follows:</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Present value of annuity</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}=\\PalAb{S}\\div(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 30%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Substitute <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\div(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 30%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Convert division&nbsp;to multiplication of fractions</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\times\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{(1+i)^n}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 30%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiply and simplify</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><br>\r\nand<br>\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Future value of annuity</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}=\\PalAa{P}\\times(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Substitute&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{P}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\times(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Convert to multiplication of fractions</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\times\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n}{1}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiply and simplify</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{S}=R\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(591,'Summary','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Summary</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">An <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">annuity</span> is a sequence of equal payments at equal intervals of time. We looked at annuities&nbsp;where the payments are made at the end of each period, known as&nbsp;annuity certain.</span><br>\r\n&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The amount or <span class=\"PalAb\"><span class=\"Emphasis_1\">future value</span></span> of an annuity is the sum of all payments made and of all&nbsp;accumulated&nbsp;</span><span class=\"BodyText\">interest at the end of the term.</span></span><br>\r\n<br>\r\n<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">If the payment in rand made at each payment interval in respect of an annuity, at interest rate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span>&nbsp;per payment interval, is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>, then the amount or <span class=\"PalAb\">future value</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((\\PalAb S)\\)</span> of the annuity after <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> intervals is&nbsp;given by the formula:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb S=R\\times\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The <span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"Emphasis_1\">present value</span></span> of an annuity is the sum of all payments, each discounted to the beginning of&nbsp;the term, that is, the sum of the present values of all payments.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nIf the payment in rand made at each payment interval in respect of an annuity, at interest rate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span>&nbsp;per payment interval, is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(R\\)</span>, then the <span class=\"PalAa\">present value</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((\\PalAa P)\\)</span> of the annuity after <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> intervals is given by&nbsp;the formula:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa P=R\\times\\left[\\displaystyle\\frac{(1+i)^n-1}{i(1+i)^n}\\right]\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">relationship</span> between the present value of an annuity and the future value of an annuity is:</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa P=\\PalAb S\\div(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">or</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb S=\\PalAa P\\times(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(592,'Instructions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Exercise instructions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"B