g2\">Assignment information</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The&nbsp;a<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">ssignment questions following the annuities&nbsp;learning unit&nbsp;contribute towards your semester mark and final mark.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">All the assignment questions for&nbsp;the relevant topics can be accessed once all the relevant learning units of the topics have been&nbsp;completed.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;has to be submitted online via myUnisa.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Refer to the tutorial letter&nbsp;for more information about the assignment.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The assignment&nbsp;consists of multiple choice questions.</span></li>\r\n<li>Click&nbsp;the &#39;Continue&#39;&nbsp;button to<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&nbsp;access the assignment questions following&nbsp;the annuities&nbsp;learning unit.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(594,'Introduction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">An introduction to simple and compound interest</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>What is the difference between <span class=\"PalAa\">simple interest</span> and <span class=\"PalAb\">compound interest</span>?</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Simple interest</span> is&nbsp;interest paid on the original principal only.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose Paul invests <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span> for three years at a simple interest rate of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span> per annum.&nbsp;Determine the simple interest that he earns.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Interest formula</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I=Pin\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Substitute the variables</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I=\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times0 \\Ndp 10\\times3 \\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Calculate</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I=\\Cur180\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>At the end he will have earned&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 180 \\Cdp 00 \\)</span> in interest.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The accrued principal (accumulated sum or&nbsp;future value) will be calculated as:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Accrued principal</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=P+I\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span>Substitute the variables</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\Cur600\\Cdp00+\\Cur180\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span>Calculate</span></th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\Cur780\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>The accrued principal (accumulated sum or&nbsp;future value) is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 780 \\Cdp 00\\)</span>. &nbsp;So actually, every year the bank started with <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00 \\)</span> to calculate the interest.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Compound interest</span> is the interest earned on the original<br>\r\n		principal,&nbsp;as well as&nbsp;on all interests earned previously.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>In other words, with compound interest, at the end of each&nbsp;year,&nbsp;the interest earned is added to the original amount and the money is reinvested.</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(595,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Simple and compound interest: Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose Paul invests&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;for three years at an interest rate of&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;per annum.&nbsp;Determine both the <span class=\"PalAa\">simple interest</span> and <span class=\"PalAb\">compound interest</span>&nbsp;that he earns.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If we determine both&nbsp;the simple and&nbsp;compound interest for this situation, the interest will be compounded as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 35%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Simple interest</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Compound interest</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest earned on original principal</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest earned on original principal<br>\r\n		+ all interests earned previously</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Original balance</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest end Year 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp1=\\PalAa{\\Cur 60 \\Cdp 00}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp1=\\PalAb{\\Cur 60 \\Cdp 00}\\)</span><br>\r\n		<span class=\"PalAb\">(leave in account)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Balance end Year 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Balance beginning Year 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest end Year 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp1=\\PalAa{\\Cur 60 \\Cdp 00}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp1=\\PalAb{\\Cur 66 \\Cdp 00}\\)</span><br>\r\n		(leave in account)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Balance end Year 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Balance beginning Year 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest end Year 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp1=\\PalAa{\\Cur 60 \\Cdp 00}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp1=\\PalAb{\\Cur 72 \\Cdp 60}\\)</span><br>\r\n		(leave in account)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Balance end Year 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 798 \\Cdp 60\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align}\\Cur600\\Cdp00&amp;+\\PalAa{\\Cur180\\Cdp00}\\\\&amp;=\\Cur780\\Cdp00\\end{align}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 798 \\Cdp 60\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align}\\Cur780\\Cdp00&amp;-\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\\\&amp;=\\PalAa{\\Cur180\\Cdp00}\\end{align}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align}\\Cur798\\Cdp60&amp;-\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\\\&amp;=\\PalAb{\\Cur198\\Cdp60}\\end{align}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(596,'Simple interest amount','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Simple interest amount</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose Paul invests <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600 \\Cdp00\\)</span> for three years at a <span class=\"PalAa\">simple interest</span> rate of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span> per annum.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We saw that for <span class=\"PalAa\">simple interest</span> the interest amount never changes; it remains the <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">same</span> for every year.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(597,'Compound interest amount','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Compound interest amount</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose Paul invests <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span> for three years at a <span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"PalAa\">compounded interest</span></span> rate of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span> per annum.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We can see that for <span class=\"PalAa\">compounded interest</span> the interest amount <span class=\"PalAa\">increases </span>every year; it is <span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"Emphasis_1\">different</span></span> every year.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Compounded interest</span> can be applied in both the following situations:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Make one investment and leave it to gain an increased amount of interest per year.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"PalAa\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Borrow one amount of money which accumulates an increased amount of interest per year.</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(598,'How it works 2','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">How compound interest works 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose Paul invests&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span>&nbsp;for three years at a&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">compounded interest</span>&nbsp;rate of&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span>&nbsp;per annum. &nbsp;Calculate the amount in his account after three years:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\">Original balance</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>Balance end Year 1</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00+(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\times{0\\Ndp10})=\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600 \\Cdp 00\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}=\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>Balance beginning Year 2</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>Balance end Year 2</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00+(\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp10)\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 660 \\Cdp 00\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}=\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>Balance beginning Year 3</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>Balance end Year 3</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00+(\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00\\times0\\Ndp10)\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 726 \\Cdp 00\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}=\\Cur 798 \\Cdp 60\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">To calculate the amount in his account in another way, let&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\( i\\)</span>&nbsp;denote the <span class=\"PalAa\">percentage interest</span> the invested&nbsp;money&nbsp;earns each year,&nbsp;where&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\( i\\)</span>&nbsp;is expressed as a decimal. Then calculate&nbsp;the <span class=\"PalAb\">compounded interest</span>. It can be concluded that each year the invested&nbsp;money is multiplied by&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{(1+i)}\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Since Paul invested his money at a&nbsp;compounded interest&nbsp;rate of&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span>&nbsp;per annum, in this example&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i=0\\Ndp10\\)</span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{(1+i)}=\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">In account after three years</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">To calculate the amount in his account after three years, we begin with our original deposit of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span> and multiply by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\)</span> a total of three times. The result is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Original deposit</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Multiply three&nbsp;times</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Exponential form</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}^3\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Calculate</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur798\\Cdp60\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">In account after five years</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So if we want to know how much he has in his account say after five years, we begin with our original deposit of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span> and multiply by <span class=\"PalAb\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp10\\)</span></span> a total of five times. The result is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span>Original deposit</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Multiply five times</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Exponential form</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times\\PalAb{1\\Ndp10}^5\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Calculate</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur966\\Cdp31\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(599,'Formula','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">A formula for calculating <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"PalAb\">Compound interest</span> yields&nbsp;better results than <span class=\"PalAa\">simple interest</span>, so you make more money. &nbsp;Compound interest is just the repeated application of simple interest to an amount which is at each stage increased by the simple interest earned in the previous period. &nbsp;But as the investment term stretches over a long period, we will have to do a lot of calculations. &nbsp;So,&nbsp;let us consider a&nbsp;formula for the general situation.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">The formula for the general situation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Suppose you deposit a principal amount&nbsp;??<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span>, at a certain annual interest rate&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span>, but&nbsp;compounded after every time period of some specified length. How&nbsp;much is your accumulated sum <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span> after <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> time periods?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We let <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> denote the percentage interest your money earns each time period.<br>\r\nThen after each time period your money is multiplied by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((1+i)\\)</span> where <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> is expressed as a decimal. &nbsp;After <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> compoundings, your money has been multiplied by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((1+i)\\)</span> a total of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> times. &nbsp;Your accumulated sum <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span>&nbsp;is given by the formula:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S=P(1+i)^n\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">where</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">is the accumulated sum/accrued principal/future value&nbsp;(total money at end of period)</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">is the principal or present value (original amount invested or borrowed)</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">is the rate of interest <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((\\%)\\)</span>&nbsp;per period, given as a decimal fraction</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right; vertical-align: top;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; vertical-align: top;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">is the number of periods of investment (term)</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>There are four variables needed when determining compound interest. &nbsp;If you know any three of these, the fourth can be determined.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The formula is not difficult to remember if you understand how it is derived. &nbsp;At each compounding the amount is multiplied by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((1+i)\\)</span>, so that after <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> compoundings the original principal <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P\\)</span> has been multiplied by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((1+i)^n\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(600,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Calculate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span>: An example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculate the accumulated sum on <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur500\\Cdp00\\)</span> invested for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\)</span> years at <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(7\\frac{1}{2}\\%\\)</span> per&nbsp;annum and compounded annually.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Write down all the information given:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 12%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Principal&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\((P)\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{principal}=\\Cur500\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P=\\Cur500\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Term&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\((n)\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{term}=10\\:\\text{years}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n=10\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest rate&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\((i)\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\text{interest rate}=7\\frac{1}{2}\\%\\:\\text{compound annually}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i=0\\Ndp075\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Use the general situation formula&nbsp;to calculate the accumulated sum <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((S)\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Formula</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\)</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(P(1+i)^n\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Substitute</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur500\\Cdp00(1+0\\Ndp075)^{10}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Calculate</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur500\\Cdp00\\times1\\Ndp075^{10}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Simplify</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur1\\Tsp030\\Cdp52\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The accumulated sum/future value is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur1\\Tsp030\\Cdp52\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(601,'Compounding periods','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Compounding periods</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Interest is not always compounded annually&nbsp;(once a year). &nbsp;Sometimes it is compounded semi-annually, quarterly, monthly, daily, even continuously. &nbsp;In these cases interest is added more frequently than once a year. &nbsp;As a result, there is more opportunity to earn interest on interest.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The mathematics remains the same, but you must be careful about what you substitute into the formula equation&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(S=P(1+i)^n\\)</span>&nbsp;for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(i\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If interest is compounded:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 25%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>annually</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">then interest is added*</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">once a year</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">semi-annually</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>then interest is added*</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">every six months</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">quarterly</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>then interest is added*</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">every three months</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">daily</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>then interest is added*</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">every day</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">*Note that the interest is added to&nbsp;the total of the original principal plus&nbsp;all interests earned previously.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The focus in this module&nbsp;is on cases where the interest is compounded annually, semi-annually, quarterly and monthly.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:06','2017-10-11 12:27:06','',NULL),(602,'Semi-annually','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Interest compounded semi-annually</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Suppose Paul invests&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;for three years at a&nbsp;</span>compounded interest<span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;rate of&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;per annum, but the interest is compounded <span class=\"PalAb\">semi-annually</span>. This means his interest is added to the principal every six months, not every year.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Principal&nbsp;after first half-year</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Calculate the amount of interest he has earned and his new principal after the first six months, or half-year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can calculate&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">the amount of interest he has earned and his new principal after the first six months in the following way:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p>Interest formula</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=P\\times i \\times n\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p><span>Interest earned after first six months</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(I\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times 0\\Ndp10\\times\\PalAb{0\\Ndp5}=\\Cur30\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p><span>New principal</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=P+I\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 50%;\">\r\n		<p><span>New principal after&nbsp;first six months</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\Cur600\\Cdp00+\\Cur30\\Cdp00=\\Cur630\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>So after the first six months, or half-year, the amount of interest he has earned is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur30\\Cdp00\\)</span>&nbsp;and his new principal is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur630\\Cdp00\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We can also calculate his new principal after the first six months in the following&nbsp;way:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For a half-year period his interest percentage is cut in <span class=\"PalAb\">half</span>&nbsp;from <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span> to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\%\\)</span>, so that the interest he earns is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span>. Thus his new principal after six months is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(105\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span>Half-year period interest&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\%\\)</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{\\PalAb2}\\text{year}\\:I=I\\div\\PalAb2=10\\%\\div2=5\\%\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span>Interest earned after first six months</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{2}\\text{year}\\:I\\times P=5\\%\\times \\Cur600\\Cdp00=\\Cur30\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span>New principal after first six months</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\left(\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{2}\\:\\text{year}\\:I+100\\%\\right)\\times P\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=(5\\%+100\\%)\\times \\Cur600\\Cdp00=105\\%\\times \\Cur600\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=1\\Ndp05\\times \\Cur600\\Cdp00=\\Cur630\\Cdp00\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, his new principal after the first&nbsp;six months&nbsp;is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur630\\Cdp00\\)</span></span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Principal&nbsp;after second half year</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">His new principal after another six months, that is after one year, is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(105\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur630\\Cdp00\\)</span>. It is calculated in the following way:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>New principal after second six months</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\left(\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{2}\\:\\text{year}\\:I+100\\%\\right)\\times (P\\:\\text{after first six months})\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=(5\\%+100\\%)\\times \\Cur630\\Cdp00=105\\%\\times \\Cur630\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=1\\Ndp05\\times \\Cur630\\Cdp00=\\Cur661\\Cdp50\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>So, his new principal after another six months, that is after one year, is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur661\\Cdp50\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Principal&nbsp;after one&nbsp;year</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The same reasoning shows that Paul&#39;s principal gets multiplied by the factor <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp05\\)</span> every half-year. After one year, two half-year periods have passed, so Paul&#39;s money has been multiplied by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\Ndp05\\)</span> twice. His principal amount after one year is calculated in the following way:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 30%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>New principal after one year</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=P\\times\\left(\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{2}\\:\\text{year}\\:I+100\\%\\right)\\times\\left(\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{2}\\:\\text{year}\\:I+100\\%\\right) \\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times105\\%\\times105\\%=\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times1\\Ndp05\\times1\\Ndp05\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times1\\Ndp05^2=\\Cur600\\Cdp00\\times1\\Ndp1025=\\Cur661\\Cdp50\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, his principal amount after one year is the same as when calculated after two&nbsp;half-year time periods, namely&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur661\\Cdp50\\)</span></span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Principal&nbsp;after three years</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">After three years, six half-year time periods have passed. So, after three years we can calculate Paul&#39;s principal in&nbsp;the same&nbsp;way:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 30%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>New principal after three years</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=P\\times\\left(\\dis