tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Interest is compounded <span class=\"PalAb\">monthly</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If Paul&#39;s interest is compounded monthly, then interest is compounded </span><span class=\"PalAb\">twelve</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;times a year (every month), so his periodic interest rate is the interest rate of&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;divided by </span><span class=\"PalAb\">twelve</span><span class=\"BodyText\">.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Monthly period interest rate</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{\\PalAb{12}}\\text{year}\\:I=I\\div\\PalAb{12}=10\\%\\div12=0\\Ndp83\\%=\\PalAb{0\\Ndp0083}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p>Principal every month</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(= P\\:\\text{from previous month}\\times(1+\\PalAb{0\\Ndp0083})=1\\Ndp0083\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consequently, every month&nbsp;(</span><span class=\"PalAb\">twelve</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;times a year) his principal is multiplied by the factor&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\((1+\\PalAb{0\\Ndp0083})=1\\Ndp0083\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span s=\"\">For interest compounded <span class=\"PalAb\">monthly</span></span><span>,&nbsp;the periodic</span><br>\r\n		<span>interest rate&nbsp;is a twelfth&nbsp;of&nbsp;the annual interest rate.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r