\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa 3\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(621,'A function','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Identifying a function</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Input, relationship and output</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Does a function always have a name, such as <span class=\"math-tex\">\\( f(x)\\)</span>&nbsp;or <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(k(p)\\)</span>? &nbsp;Sometimes a function has no name, and you might just see something like:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y=3\\PalAb x +2\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">However, we still have:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">an <span class=\"PalAb\">input</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 30%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">a relationship</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">multiplying by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span>&nbsp;and adding <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 30%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">and an <span class=\"PalAa\">output</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Single value result</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">There is another important concept about a function&nbsp;we need to consider, namely a&nbsp;function may&nbsp;only result in a single value for the dependent variable.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, does the formula <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y=3\\PalAb x +2\\)</span> represent a function? &nbsp;Yes&nbsp;it does,&nbsp;because every time that you substitute a number for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span>, you will only get a single value for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">To illustrate, we can substitute&nbsp;different values for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span> and get different&nbsp;single values for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Formula</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\PalAb x+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Let&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x = \\PalAb 3\\)</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3(\\PalAb 3)+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\times\\PalAb 3+2=9+2=\\PalAa{11}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">When&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x = \\PalAb 3\\)</span>, then</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{11}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Let&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x = \\PalAb 7\\)</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3(\\PalAb 7)+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\times\\PalAb 7+2=21+2=\\PalAa{23}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>When&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x = \\PalAb 7\\)</span><span>, then</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{23}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, we see that when <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span> equals <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb 3\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span> equals <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{11}\\)</span> every time. &nbsp;No other number will correspond with <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb 3\\)</span>, when using this formula.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">And if we&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">input</span> another number, like&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb 7\\)</span>, we&nbsp;get a different <span class=\"PalAa\">output</span>. &nbsp;When <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span> equals&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb 7\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span> equals <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{23}\\)</span> every time. &nbsp;No other number will correspond with <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb 7\\)</span>, when using this formula.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Therefore, this formula can be labelled a function.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This seems straightforward. &nbsp;It would seem&nbsp;like all formulas could be considered functions. &nbsp;However, this&nbsp;is&nbsp;not always the case.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(622,'Not a function','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Identifying when not a function</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">A function may only result in <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">one</span>&nbsp;single<br>\r\n		value&nbsp;for the dependent variable.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">It might&nbsp;seem&nbsp;like all formulas could be considered functions. &nbsp;However, this&nbsp;is&nbsp;not always the case, as can be seen in the following illustration:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the formula</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y^2\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">or</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\pm \\sqrt{x}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">which is</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\( \\sqrt{x}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">and</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(- \\sqrt{x}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">When <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x=\\PalAb 4\\)</span>, we get</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y^2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">or</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\pm \\sqrt{4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">which is</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\( \\sqrt{4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">and</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(- \\sqrt{4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\( \\sqrt{2\\times2}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(- \\sqrt{2\\times2}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-2\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 45%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>So&nbsp;when&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x=\\PalAb 4\\)</span><span>, we get</span></span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa 2\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">and</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{-2}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Look at the three parts of this formula <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y^2=\\PalAb x\\)</span>&nbsp;(or&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y=\\pm \\sqrt{\\PalAb x}\\)</span>) for different values of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Input<br>\r\n		(independent variable)</span></span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Relationship</span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Output<br>\r\n		(dependent variable)</span></span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\({\\pm \\sqrt{\\PalAb{4}}}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa2\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{-2}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb6\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\({\\pm \\sqrt{\\PalAb{6}}}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{2\\Ndp45}\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{-2\\Ndp45}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{16}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\({\\pm \\sqrt{\\PalAb{16}}}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa4\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{-4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Each time we input a value of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>, we get two different answers for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span>. As we can see,&nbsp;when <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span> equals <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span> equals <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-2\\)</span> and so forth.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Therefore, the formula <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y^2=\\PalAb x\\)</span> does <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">not</span> represent a function, because for each positive <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span> there are <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">two</span> values for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(623,'Independent variables','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Functions with multiple independent variables</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Functions can have more than one <span class=\"PalAb\">independent</span> variable.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Functions of one independent variable</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following function is a function of one independent variable:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 30%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 5%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y=f(\\PalAb x)=\\PalAb x+3\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">where</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 63%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">independent</span>&nbsp;variable</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 30%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">and</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 63%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">dependent</span>&nbsp;variable.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\"><br>\r\nFunctions of multiple independent variables</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following functions are all functions of&nbsp;more than one independent variable:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"4\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=f(x,z)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5x-4z\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(w=g(x,y,z)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3xy^2z^3\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(h(x_1,x_2,x_3,x_4)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4x_1-2x_2-5x_3+x_4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Note that&nbsp;the notation used for functions of several variables is similar to the notation used for&nbsp;single variable functions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br>\r\n<span class=\"BodyText\">The following function is a function of <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">two</span>&nbsp;variables:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 18%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 10%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y=f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAb z)=5\\PalAb x-4\\PalAb z\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 18%; text-align: right;\">where</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb z\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">are the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAb\">independent</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;variables</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 18%; text-align: right;\">and</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">dependent</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;variable.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><br>\r\n<span class=\"BodyText\">Likewise, the following function is a function of <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">three</span>&nbsp;variables:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 18%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 15%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa w=g(\\PalAb x,\\PalAb y,\\PalAb z)=3\\PalAb{xy}^2\\PalAb{z}^3\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 18%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">where</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 17%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb y\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb z\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">are the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">independent</span>&nbsp;variables</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 18%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">and</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 17%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa w\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">dependent</span>&nbsp;variable.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><br>\r\n<span class=\"BodyText\">The function <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(h\\)</span> is similar except there are <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">four</span> independent variables.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(624,'Notation','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Specific form of function</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">How do you write a function?</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Is the following function written as</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 8%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: right;\">or</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: right;\">or written as</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z=f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span>?</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In function notation all independent variables are listed in the brackets, separated by commas or semicolons. In this notation:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The function is written as</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z=f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">which is read as</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">&quot;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\)</span> is a function of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span>&quot;.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Specific form of the function</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">However, take note&nbsp;that with this notation no information with regard&nbsp;to the specific form of the function is conveyed. &nbsp;It is merely stated that <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\)</span> is the <span class=\"PalAa\">dependent variable</span> which is a function of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\( x\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span>. &nbsp;In this sense the notation does not discriminate between the above function&nbsp;and any other function of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The function is only completely specified once the <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">functional form</span> or <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">relationship</span>, that is the rule for determining the value of the <span class=\"PalAa\">dependent variable</span> from the values of the <span class=\"PalAb\">independent variables</span>, is given.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Thus a complete specification of this&nbsp;function&nbsp;is written as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">If the function is</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span>,</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">then the complete specification is</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z=f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Purpose of function notation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Why then do we use this notation <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z=f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)\\)</span> if it does not convey complete information about the function?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The answer is that the notation provides us with a concise and clear way of indicating that in a particular function, which has been previously defined, particular numerical values are to be substituted for the <span class=\"PalAb\">independent variables</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(625,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Substitute values for variables</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Function notation shows us how to substitute particular numerical values for each <span class=\"PalAb\">independent variable</span> in a specific function.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If we consider the function&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z=f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)=6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span>, then&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb2;\\PalAa3)\\)</span>&nbsp;means that&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb2\\)</span>&nbsp;is substituted for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa 3\\)</span>&nbsp;is substituted for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span>. &nbsp;The&nbsp;value of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb2;\\PalAa3)\\)</span>&nbsp;is then calculated as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">If the function is</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 12%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">then&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb2;\\PalAa3)\\)</span>&nbsp;is</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb2;\\PalAa3)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6(\\PalAb2)-3(\\PalAa3)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Calculate and simplify</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\times\\PalAb2-3\\times\\PalAa3\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(12-9\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Similarly, the value of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb{5\\Ndp5};\\PalAa{4\\Ndp5})\\)</span>&nbsp;is&nbsp;calculated as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>If function is</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(z\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 12%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb x,\\PalAa y)\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\PalAb x-3\\PalAa y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">then&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb{5\\Ndp5};\\PalAa{4\\Ndp5})\\)</span>&nbsp;is</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(\\PalAb{5\\Ndp5};\\PalAa{4\\Ndp5})\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6(\\PalAb{5\\Ndp5})-3(\\PalAa{4\\Ndp5})\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Calculate and simplify</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(6\\times\\PalAb{5\\Ndp5}-3\\times\\PalAa{4\\Ndp5}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(33-13\\Ndp5\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 40%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(19\\Ndp5\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Note that confusion may arise when&nbsp;using the decimal, so&nbsp;we rather use a semicolon <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((;)\\)</span> instead of&nbsp;a comma <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((,)\\)</span> to separate variables.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(626,'Graphing functions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Graphing of functions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We have all&nbsp;heard bold statements and predictions such as the following on the news and in advertisements:</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&quot;Fluoride toothpaste prevents cavities.&quot;</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">&quot;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(45\\Tsp000\\)</span> university graduates will buy new cars in December.&quot;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Have you ever stopped to wonder how these claims were reached? &nbsp;How was it concluded that smoking and cancer are related? &nbsp;How can it be&nbsp;predicted how many new cars will be sold?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">To help making such predictions, we can use functions. &nbsp;We can graph these functions as well.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Graphing functions is a visual way of representing&nbsp;relationships<br>\r\n		between variables.&nbsp;A graph basically summarizes <em>how&nbsp;one<br>\r\n		quantity changes&nbsp;if&nbsp;other quantities related to it&nbsp;also&nbsp;change.</em></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Graphs and functions are very useful in the financial world. &nbsp;A function is the mathematical expression that describes the relationship between two or more variables. &nbsp;By graphing the function you show the relationship in a picture.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In real life, whenever a relationship between two variables exists and is known, one variable can be used to guess the other. &nbsp;You sometimes see in the media a graph with a straight line that is going up or down. &nbsp;What does this mean? A straight line shows you a picture of the relationship between two variables and helps you to make predictions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">An example is the relationship between the price of a product and the quantity consumers are willing to buy. &nbsp;At lower prices, consumers may be willing to buy more, but buy less as prices increase.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"650\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/101.html\" width=\"670\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(627,'Introduction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Introduction</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Ren&eacute; Descartes was a French man who lived in the 1600s. &nbsp;He invented the&nbsp;rectangular coordinate system or plane. &nbsp;In fact, this coordinate system is sometimes called the Cartesian plane&nbsp;in his honour. &nbsp;Using this plane, we can describe any&nbsp;point in the plane using an ordered pair of numbers.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The Cartesian plane is like a map grid. &nbsp;You can locate any point in the Cartesian plane if you know two things:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">how far the point is to the </span>left or right<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">, and</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">how far the point is </span>up or down<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Let us start by looking at a map, given below. &nbsp;In this city map, the Town Hall is right at the centre of the town. &nbsp;As you travel east of the centre of town, the streets are named <span class=\"PalAa\">10th&nbsp;Street East</span>, <span class=\"PalAa\">11th Street East</span> and so forth. &nbsp;You find similar patterns as you drive west, north or south. &nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">Middle Street</span> is really zero east and zero west simultaneously, so it is easiest to just give it a name. &nbsp;Similarly, <span class=\"PalAb\">Main Road</span> is simultaneously zero north and zero south.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/26.svg\" style=\"height: 383px; width: 650px;\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You can easily find any location on the map just by knowing how far it is east or west and north or south of the centre of town. The car is at about the crossing of <span class=\"PalAa\">11th Street East</span> and <span class=\"PalAb\">11th Street North</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">For the Cartesian plane we use positive and negative numbers. &nbsp;If <span class=\"PalAa\">Middle Street</span> is at zero east and west,&nbsp;and <span class=\"PalAb\">Main Road</span> is at&nbsp;zero north and south, then east and north will be&nbsp;positive while west and south will be&nbsp;negative.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(628,'Amortisation','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Amortisation</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(629,'Annuities','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Annuities</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(630,'Compound interest','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Compound interest</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(631,'Definition of functions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Definition of functions</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(632,'Linear functions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Linear functions</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-10-11 12:27:07','',NULL),(633,'Test Pages','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ1OTIzNjA0MTE3MDIyNzgwIn0=\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:07','2017-12-15 10:34:47','',NULL),(634,'Exponential and logarithmic functions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Exponential and logarithmic functions</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 1