an class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa f\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Image\">\r\n		<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/46.svg\"></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{f^{-1}}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Image\">\r\n		<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/45.svg\"></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(706,'Equation','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Equation</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The logarithmic function is very closely related to the exponential function. &nbsp;Logarithms are simply another way to write exponents.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Exponential function</span></th>\r\n		<th scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 7%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Logarithmic function</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{f(x)=a^x=y}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">with&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a&gt;0\\)</span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a \\neq1\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">then</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{log_ay=x}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">with&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y&gt;0\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 3%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 6%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">To what power (</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{x}\\)</span><span class=\"PalAa\">) must</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa a\\)</span> <span class=\"PalAa\">be raised, to get an answer of</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span><span class=\"PalAa\">?</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 7%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAb\">The logarithm of</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb y\\)</span> <span class=\"PalAb\">to the base</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb a\\)</span> <span class=\"PalAb\">is</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span><span class=\"PalAb\">.</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 6%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" colspan=\"5\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"PalAb\">logarithmic</span> (or <span class=\"PalAb\">log</span> as it is often referred to) function is completely determined by the corresponding <span class=\"PalAa\">exponential</span> function. &nbsp;They are <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">inverse</span> functions.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 6%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Read from&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{x}\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">to</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 7%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Read back from&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb y\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">to</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 6%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{f(x)=a^x}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 2%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 7%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"width: 25%; text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{f^{-1}(y)=\\log_ay}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/47.svg\"></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(707,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Evaluate the expression <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_{10}100\\)</span> without using a calculator. &nbsp;Note that the <span class=\"PalBa\">base</span> is equal to&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa{10}\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 28%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Set the log equal to&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBb x\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_{\\PalBa{10}}\\PalBc{100}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBb x\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">To what <span class=\"PalCb\">power</span> must <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\)</span> be raised to get <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\)</span>?</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 28%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Use the definition of log to write the equation in exponential form.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa{10}\\PalBb{^x}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{100}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Definition of log:&nbsp;If <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc y=\\PalBa a \\PalBb{^x}\\)</span> with <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a&gt;0\\)</span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a \\neq1\\)</span>, then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log\\PalBa{_a} \\PalBc y= \\PalBb x\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 28%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Solve for&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBb x\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa{10} \\PalBb{^x}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10^x\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10^x\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc{100}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10 \\times10\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10^2\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 28%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">From this</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBb x\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 3%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBb 2\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Therefore,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_{10}100=2\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalBb\">exponent&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBb{=2}\\)</span></span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">If</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa{10} \\PalBb{^2}= \\PalBc{100}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">then</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_{\\PalBa{10}}\\PalBc{100}=\\PalBb2\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalBa\">base&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa{=10}\\)</span></span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, a logarithm gives you the <span class=\"PalBb\">exponent</span> as its answer.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(708,'In general','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">In general</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Regarding <span class=\"PalAa\">exponents</span>, any number raised to the <span class=\"PalAa\">power of one</span>, is equal to <span class=\"PalAa\">the number</span> and any number raised to the <span class=\"PalAb\">power of zero</span>, is equal to <span class=\"PalAb\">one</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therefore, for <span class=\"PalAb\">logarithms</span> there are two general results in particular:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">Because&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\PalAa{^1}=\\PalAa a\\)</span>, it follows that&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_a\\PalAb a=\\PalAb1\\)</span>,<br>\r\n		and<br>\r\n		because&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a^\\PalAa0=\\PalAa1\\)</span>, it follows that <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_a\\PalAb1=\\PalAb0\\)</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">Note that the base in the two cases above is equal to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">When the base is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\)</span> you get the <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">common logarithm</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_{10}y\\)</span>, which is sometimes just written as <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log y\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">When the base is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(e\\)</span>, you get the <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">natural logarithm</span>. &nbsp;The calculator has a key for&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_e\\)</span> which is usually&nbsp;<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">denoted by the symbol <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(ln\\)</span>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">(The symbol <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(e\\)</span> is a famous number in mathematics. &nbsp;It is called Euler&#39;s number and approximates to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\Ndp718\\)</span>.)</span></span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">In computer science we have <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(lg\\)</span> which is the logarithm base <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span>, or <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_2\\)</span>.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(709,'Graph','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Graphing functions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>What does the graph of the logarithmic function look like?&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the <span class=\"PalAa\">exponential function</span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(x)=2^x\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In this case the base is equal to&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span>. &nbsp;The <span class=\"PalAb\">logarithmic function</span> is the <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">inverse</span> of the <span class=\"PalAa\">exponential function</span>. &nbsp;Remember&nbsp;that the inverse function should give you back the original value that was put into the function. &nbsp;Therefore, if <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{(4;16)}\\)</span> is a point on the graph of an <span class=\"PalAa\">exponential function</span>, then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{(16;4)}\\)</span> would be the corresponding point on the graph of the <span class=\"PalAb\">logarithmic function</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Look at the following explanation, using this&nbsp;exponential function:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style1\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<thead>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th colspan=\"5\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 20%;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">Exponential function</span></th>\r\n		<th colspan=\"5\" rowspan=\"1\" scope=\"col\" style=\"width: 8%;\"><span class=\"PalAb\">Logarithmic function</span></th>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 16%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 16%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f^{-1}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 16%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2^{-1}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(0\\Ndp5\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 16%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\log_2{0 \\Ndp5}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"5\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{-1}\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">goes in and</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{0\\Ndp5}\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">comes out</span></td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"5\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 8%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAb\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{0\\Ndp5}\\)</span>&nbsp;goes in and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{-1}\\)</span>&nbsp;comes out</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 16%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAa\">The point is&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{(-1;0\\Ndp5)}\\)</span><span class=\"PalAa\">.</span></td>\r\n		<td colspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 8%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"PalAb\">The point is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{(0\\Ndp5;-1)}\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This is illustrated in the following graph:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"412\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/195.html\" width=\"412\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(710,'Video 1','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch the first part of this video on solving linear equations in one variable:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/301.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(711,'Video 2','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">