\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(A\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td class=\"Table_Number\" style=\"text-align: center; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 18%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>In each case the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAb\">values</span><span>&nbsp;on the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAb\">right</span><span>&nbsp;(the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAb\">solutions</span><span>)&nbsp;</span><span>make the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">statements</span><span>&nbsp;on the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">left</span><span>&nbsp;(the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">equations</span><span>) true.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The process of determining which values of the variables make the statement true is known as&nbsp;<span class=\"Emphasis_1\">solving the equation</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(713,'Steps','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Steps</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following eight steps can be used to solve a linear equation in one variable:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Remove the brackets if any.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Add like terms.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Eliminate any constants on the left-hand side of the equation by adding its additive inverse to both&nbsp;sides of the equation.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 4</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Add like terms.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 5</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Eliminate any variable on the right-hand side of the equation by adding its additive inverse to both&nbsp;sides of the equation.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 6</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Add like terms.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 7</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If the coefficient of the variable is not one,&nbsp;multiply each side of the equation by the reciprocal&nbsp;of the coefficient.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 8</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Solve the equation.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(714,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The following example demonstrates setting up your own linear equation. &nbsp;A linear equation can be formed by converting a word statement to a linear equation:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">&quot;The <span class=\"PalAa\">first</span><span class=\"PalAa\"> </span>number is three less than two times the <span class=\"PalAb\">second</span><span class=\"PalAb\"> </span>number. &nbsp;If their sum is&nbsp;increased by seven, the result is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37\\)</span>. &nbsp;Find the numbers.&quot;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Determine the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAb\">second</span>&nbsp;number</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 58%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Let&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span><span>&nbsp;be the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAb\">second</span><span>&nbsp;number.</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"5\" style=\"width: 5%;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"BodyText\">&quot;The&nbsp;first&nbsp;number is three less than&nbsp;two&nbsp;times the&nbsp;second&nbsp;number.&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>So, the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">first</span><span>&nbsp;number is three less than two times&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span><span>, giving the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">first</span><span style=\"font-family: \'Computer Modern Serif\'; font-size: 18px; line-height: 27px; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;number as:</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: bottom; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa2\\PalAb x\\PalAa{-3}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"5\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Emphasis_1\">&quot;If their sum...&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>The sum of the&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAa\">first</span><span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalAb\">second</span><span>&nbsp;number is:</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\((\\PalAa2\\PalAb x\\PalAa{-3})+\\PalAb x\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\PalAb x-3+\\PalAb x\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\PalAb x-3\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"5\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"Emphasis_1\">&quot;If their sum is increased by seven, the result is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37\\)</span>.&quot;</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">This gives the equation:</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\((3\\PalAb x-3)+7\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\PalAb x-3+7\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\PalAb x+4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\PalAb x+4-4\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37-4\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\PalAb x\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(33\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{3\\PalAb x}{3}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\displaystyle\\frac{33}{3}\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(11\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">So, the <span class=\"PalAb\">second</span> number is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{11}\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; vertical-align: bottom;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Determine the <span class=\"PalAa\">first</span>&nbsp;number</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 58%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"PalAa\">first</span> number is:</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa2\\PalAb x\\PalAa{-3}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa2(\\PalAb {11})\\PalAa{-3}\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\times11-3\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(22-3\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(19\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">So, the first number is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{19}\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The numbers are <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{19}\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{11}\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Check the numbers</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>These numbers can be checked as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 42%; text-align: left; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p>It is true that <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{19}=2(\\PalAb{11})-3\\)</span>,</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p>The first requirement, &quot;the <span class=\"PalAa\">first</span> number is three less than two times the <span class=\"PalAb\">second</span>&quot;,&nbsp;is satisfied.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>and</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\">it is true that <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{19}+\\PalAb{11}+7=37\\)</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\to\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The second requirement, &quot;if their sum is increased by seven, the result is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(37\\)</span>&quot;, is satisfied.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(715,'Determine  x-intercept','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Solving linear equations by using <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>-intercepts</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Linear equations can be solved with a&nbsp;step-by-step method, however&nbsp;there is no reason why short-cuts and and adding&nbsp;several terms at once cannot be used. &nbsp;However, if you are unsure about using alternative methods,&nbsp;rather be on the safe side and work step by step. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A linear equation&nbsp;can be solved by determining the&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>-intercept of the corresponding line. &nbsp;This is another method of solving&nbsp;linear equations in one variable. &nbsp;Any linear equation <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=ax+b\\)</span>&nbsp;can be solved by using this method:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"width: 85%;\">\r\n		<p>Manipulate the linear equation, using&nbsp;operations, until it is in the form:</p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(ax+b=0\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n		<p>The left-hand side is the general equation for a linear function.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15px;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<p>This equation is solved by adding <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-b\\)</span> to both sides to get:</p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align}ax+b-b&amp;=-b\\\\ ax&amp;=-b \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n		<p>Divide by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>, assuming <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\neq0\\)</span>, to obtain the root or solution:</p>\r\n\r\n		<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x={\\displaystyle-\\frac{b}{a}}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The last equation in this&nbsp;method&nbsp;is&nbsp;the equation for the intercept on the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>-axis of the linear function <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=ax+b\\)</span>. &nbsp;This intercept occurs at <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=0\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">In other words, we can always interpret the root of a linear equation in one variable as the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>-intercept of the corresponding linear function as shown below:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/49.svg\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The equation of the line in this graph is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=ax+b\\)</span>. &nbsp;At the&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>-intercept point&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=0\\)</span>, therefore&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(ax+b=0\\)</span> and the value of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span> is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\({-\\displaystyle\\frac{b}{a}}\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(716,'Introduction','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Introduction</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The graph of a linear equation is a straight line. &nbsp;A solution of a linear equation will be any <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((x;y)\\)</span> point that will make the equation true. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">To illustrate, consider the graph of the line:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}x+2\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"450\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/211.html\" width=\"550\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider point&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{(0;2)}\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"Emphasis_1\">on</span> the line:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 55%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Equation of the line</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}\\PalAa x+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Substitute&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa x=\\PalAa0\\)</span>&nbsp;into the equation</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}(\\PalAa 0)+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}\\times\\PalAa 0+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=2\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, if&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa x=\\PalAa0\\)</span>, then&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa y=\\PalAa2\\)</span>, which is <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">true</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider point&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{(2;2)}\\)</span>&nbsp;<span class=\"Emphasis_1\">not</span> on the line:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 55%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Equation of the line</span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}\\PalAb x+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span>Substitute&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x=\\PalAb2\\)</span><span>&nbsp;into the equation</span></span></th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}(\\PalAb 2)+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}\\times\\PalAb 2+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=-1\\Ndp5+2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=0\\Ndp5\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>So, if&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb x=\\PalAb2\\)</span>, then&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb y=\\PalAb{0\\Ndp5}\\)</span>, which is <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">not</span> equal to <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span>&nbsp;and therefore <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">not</span> true.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In fact, all the points&nbsp;marked in <span class=\"PalAa\">blue</span>&nbsp;on the line&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=-\\displaystyle\\frac{3}{4}x+2\\)</span>&nbsp;are&nbsp;solutions of the linear equation. &nbsp;There is actually no limit to the number of solutions, since there is no limit to the number of points on the line.</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">Every point on the line graph is a solution of the linear equation and any solution of the linear equation is a point on the line graph.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(717,'The system','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Defining a system of linear equations in two variables</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">What is a <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">system of linear equations in two variables</span>?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">It is a set or collection of linear equations whose common solutions are looked for. &nbsp;The simplest linear system is one with two equations and two variables. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We can also refer to this kind of system&nbsp;as&nbsp;<span class=\"Emphasis_1\">simultaneous linear equations</span>&nbsp;or a <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">linear system</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Consider the following system with two linear equations and two variables:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{y=\\displaystyle\\frac{5}{2}x-5}\\)</span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb{y=-x+1}\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Since the two equations are in a system, we work with them at the same time. &nbsp;In particular, we can graph them together on the same set of axes:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"450\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/212.html\" width=\"500\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">A solution for a single equation is any point that lies on the line for that equation. &nbsp;A solution for a system of equations is any point that lies on each line in the system. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">For example, note the following three points on the graph:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBa\">turquoise&nbsp;point</span> is not a solution of the system, because it is not on either line.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The&nbsp;<span class=\"PalBb\">purple point</span> is also not a solution of the system, because it lies on only one of the lines, not on both of them.</span></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">The <span class=\"PalBc\">green&nbsp;point</span> is a solution of the system, because it lies on both of the lines. &nbsp;In particular, this point is the intersection of the two lines. &nbsp;Since this point is on both lines,&nbsp;it satisfies (or is a solution of) both equations. &nbsp;So it satisfies the entire system of equations.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">For systems of equations, the&nbsp;<span class=\"Emphasis_1\">solutions</span>&nbsp;are the points of <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">intersections</span> of the corresponding lines.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">You can confirm the solution by plugging it into the system of equations&nbsp;and confirming that the solution satisfies each equation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(718,'Video','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch this video on solving systems of linear equations in two variables - method of graphing:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\">\r\n<video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/308.mp4\" width=\"650\">&nbsp;</video>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(719,'Video','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch this video on solving a system of linear equations with substitution:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/309.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(720,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Use <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">substitution</span> to solve the system of linear equations:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} 5x-y&amp;=1\\\\ 4x-y&amp;=-1 \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Method</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Isolate a variable in an equation.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Substitute the result of Step 1 into the other equation and solve for one variable.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Substitute the result of Step 2 into the result of Step 1 and solve for the other variable.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 4</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">State the solution.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Solution</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Use&nbsp;substitution&nbsp;to solve the following system of linear equations:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\begin{align} \\PalCc{5x-y}&amp;\\PalCc=\\PalCc1\\\\ \\PalCd{ 4x-y}&amp;\\PalCd{=-1} \\end{align}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 47%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Isolate <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa y\\)</span> in the <span class=\"PalCc\">first equation</span>:</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 13%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{5x-}\\PalCa y\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc1\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">(subtract <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5x\\)</span> both sides)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-\\PalCa y\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-5x+1\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">(divide both sides by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1\\)</span>)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa y\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5x-1\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Step 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>Substitute result of Step 1&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {y=\\PalCa5x-1}\\)</span>&nbsp;into <span class=\"PalCd\">second equation</span> and find&nbsp;value of&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb x\\)</span>:</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\( \\PalCd{ 4\\PalCb x-\\PalCa y}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{-1}\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>(substitute <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {y=\\PalCa5x-1}\\)</span> in)</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\( 4\\PalCb x-(\\PalCa {5x-1})\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\( 4\\PalCb x-5\\PalCb x+1\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>(subtract <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\)</span> both sides)</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-\\PalCb x+1-1\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1-1\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-\\PalCb x\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-2\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p>(divide both sides by <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1\\)</span>)</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb x\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p>Step 3</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Substitute&nbsp;result of Step 2&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb{x=2}\\)</span>&nbsp;into result of Step 1&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {y=\\PalCa5x-1}\\)</span> and&nbsp;find value of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa y\\)</span>:</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {y}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {=}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa{5\\PalCb x-1}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">(substitute <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb{x=2}\\)</span> in)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {y}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5(\\PalCb2)-1\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">(calculate and simplify)</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {y}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10-1\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</th>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 20%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa {y}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(9\\)</span></span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p>Step 4</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Since <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb{x=2}\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa{y=9}\\)</span>, the solution is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((2;9)\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%; text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">When the lines are drawn you can see that they intersect at <span class=\"math-tex\">\\((2;9)\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"650\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/214.html\" width=\"550\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(721,'Video 1','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch the first part of this video on solving a system of linear equations by elimination:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/306.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(722,'Video 2','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Video 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Watch the last part of this video on s</span>olving a system of linear equations by elimination:</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Video\"><video controls=\"\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/307.mp4\" width=\"650\"></video></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:08','2017-10-11 12:27:08','',NULL),(723,'Example','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">There are many situations or problems in the business environment where the values of some unknown quantities have to be found. &nbsp;We can represent the unknown quantities by the names of two variables and form two linear equations involving the variables.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">A company publishes two magazines, namely&nbsp;<em>Fresh Food</em> and <em>Big Bite</em>. &nbsp;It costs <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur4\\Cdp00\\)</span> to print a copy of <em>Fresh Food</em> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur6\\Cdp00\\)</span> to bind it. &nbsp;It costs <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur5\\Cdp00\\)</span> to print a copy of <em>Big Bite</em> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur3\\Cdp00\\)</span> to bind it. &nbsp;The budget of the company only allows <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur21\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\)</span> for binding and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur20\\Tsp000\\Cdp00\\)</span> for printing.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Set up two linear equations that will determine how many copies of each magazine can&nbsp;be published.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Solution</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Let <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa x\\)</span> represent the number of <span class=\"PalCa\"><em>Fresh Food</em></span> magazines that are&nbsp;published.<br>\r\nLet <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb y\\)</span> represent the number of <span class=\"PalCb\"><em>Big Bite</em></span> magazines that are published.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The budget of the company only allows <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{\\Cur20\\Tsp000\\Cdp00}\\)</span> for <span class=\"PalCc\">printing</span>. &nbsp;It costs <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{\\Cur4\\Cdp00}\\)</span> to <span class=\"PalCc\">print</span> a copy&nbsp;of <span class=\"PalCa\"><em>Fresh Food</em></span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{\\Cur5\\Cdp00}\\)</span> to <span class=\"PalCc\">print</span> a copy of <span class=\"PalCb\"><em>Big Bite</em></span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The <span class=\"PalCc\">equation</span> that represents the cost and budget for <span class=\"PalCc\">printing</span> is:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{\\Cur4\\Cdp00}\\times\\)</span>&nbsp;<em style=\"color: rgb(17,\r\n 150,\r\n 179); font-family: \'Computer Modern Serif\'; font-size: 18px; line-height: 27px;\">Fresh Food</em>&nbsp;printed</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(+\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{\\Cur5\\Cdp00}\\times\\)</span>&nbsp;<em>Big Bite</em>&nbsp;printed</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 15%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{\\Cur20\\Tsp000\\Cdp00}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc 4\\PalCa x\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(+\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc 5\\PalCb y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc{20\\Tsp000}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">So, the <span class=\"PalCc\">equation</span> that represents the cost and budget for <span class=\"PalCc\">printing</span> is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc {4x+5y=20\\Tsp000} \\)</span>. Name this <span class=\"PalCc\">equation one</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The budget of the company only allows&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{\\Cur21\\Tsp000\\Cdp00}\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;for&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalCd\">binding</span><span class=\"BodyText\">. &nbsp;It costs&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{\\Cur6\\Cdp00}\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;to <span class=\"PalCd\">bind</span>&nbsp;a copy&nbsp;of&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalCa\"><em>Fresh Food</em></span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{\\Cur3\\Cdp00}\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;to <span class=\"PalCd\">bind</span>&nbsp;a copy of&nbsp;</span><span class=\"PalCb\"><em>Big Bite</em></span><span class=\"BodyText\">.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<span class=\"PalCd\">equation</span>&nbsp;that represents the cost and budget for <span class=\"PalCd\">binding</span>&nbsp;is:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{\\Cur6\\Cdp00}\\times\\)</span>&nbsp;<em>Fresh Food</em> bound</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">+</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left; width: 35%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{\\Cur3\\Cdp00}\\times\\)</span>&nbsp;<em><span class=\"PalCb\">Big Bite</span></em>&nbsp;bound</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{\\Cur21\\Tsp000\\Cdp00}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd 6\\PalCa x\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(+\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd 3\\PalCb y\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{21\\Tsp000}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>So, the&nbsp;<span class=\"PalCd\">equation</span>&nbsp;that represents the cost and budget for <span class=\"PalCd\">binding</span>&nbsp;is&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd {6x+3y=21\\Tsp000} \\)</span>. Name this&nbsp;<span class=\"PalCd\">equation two</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:09','2017-10-11 12:27:09','',NULL),(724,'&gt; and &lt;','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(&gt;\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(&lt;\\)</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 27%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The concept</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 37%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is denoted by the symbol</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa&gt;\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">The concept</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"PalAb\">less than</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">is denoted by the symbol</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAb&lt;\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">We say <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span> if and only if the difference <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b-a\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAa\">positive</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Thus&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\PalAa &gt;a\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 40%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">So,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\PalAa&gt;2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">means</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b-a\\PalAa&gt;0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">.</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">gives&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4-2=2\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\PalAa&gt;0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">.</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">We say <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAb\">less than</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span> if and only if the difference <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b-a\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAb\">negative</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">Thus</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\PalAb &lt;a\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 40%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">So,&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\PalAb&lt;4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">means</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b-a\\PalAb&lt;0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">.</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">gives <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2-4=-2\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-2\\PalAb&lt;0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">.</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">If <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b=a\\)</span> or <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a=b\\)</span> then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span> are the same number.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:09','2017-10-11 12:27:09','',NULL),(725,'&quot;&gt; and =&quot; and &quot;&lt; and =&quot;','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\geq\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\leq\\)</span></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Sometimes the symbol <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span> is combined with <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(&gt;\\)</span> or <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(&lt;\\)</span> as follows:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\PalAa{\\geq} a\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">means</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b-a \\PalAa{\\geq} 0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is <span class=\"PalAa\">greater than or equal</span> to</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>,</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\PalAb{\\leq} a\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 10%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">means</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%; text-align: left;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b-a \\PalAb{\\leq} 0\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 15%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 35%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">is <span class=\"PalAb\">less than or equal</span> to</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 5%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>.</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">If we replace the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(=\\)</span> sign in any equation, or system of equations, with a&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(&gt;\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(&lt;\\)</span>, <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\geq\\)</span> or <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\leq\\)</span>, then we obtain an <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">inequality</span> or <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">system of inequalities</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The inequality, or system of inequalities, is linear or non-linear depending on whether the functions involved are linear or non-linear.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:09','2017-10-11 12:27:09','',NULL),(726,'Rules 1 &amp; 2','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Solving an inequality: Rules 1 and 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Just like with equations, the solution to an inequality is a value that makes the inequality true.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">For example, if the inequality <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5x-15&lt;0\\)</span>&nbsp;had to be solved, it means that you have to determine the values of&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span>&nbsp;for which this statement is true.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">How is this done? &nbsp;You can solve inequalities in the same way you can solve equations, by following these&nbsp;rules.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Rules to solve inequalities</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span> is greater than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>, then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span> is less than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 18%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span> is greater than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span> is greater than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span> then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span> is greater than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You may add the same number to both sides of an inequality.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 4</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You may multiply or divide both sides of an inequality by any positive number.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 5</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">When you multiply or divide both sides of an inequality by a&nbsp;negative number, reverse the direction of the inequality sign.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Rule 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">If&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is <span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">, then&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is <span class=\"PalAb\">less than</span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n		<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n		<tbody>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">If</span></td>\r\n				<td style=\"width: 20%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\PalAa&gt;a\\)</span></span></td>\r\n				<td style=\"width: 30%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4\\PalAa&gt;1\\)</span></span></td>\r\n				<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n			<tr>\r\n				<td style=\"width: 30%; text-align: right;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">then</span></td>\r\n				<td style=\"width: 20%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\PalAb &lt;b\\)</span></span></td>\r\n				<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1\\PalAb &lt;4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n				<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			</tr>\r\n		</tbody>\r\n		</table>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Although you might say that this is obvious, it is nevertheless very useful at times when we want to interchange the left- and right-hand sides.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Rule 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\"><span class=\"BodyText\">If&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is <span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is&nbsp;<span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;then&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is <span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span>&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right; width: 30%;\">If&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 20%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\PalAa&gt;a\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 30%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(23\\PalAa&gt;21\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">and</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\PalAa&gt;c\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(21\\PalAa&gt;20\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">then</td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\PalAa&gt;c\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(23\\PalAa&gt;20\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If your sister is older than you and you are older than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\)</span> years, then your sister must also be older than <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(20\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:09','2017-10-11 12:27:09','',NULL),(727,'Rule 5','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Solving an inequality: Rule 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You can solve inequalities in the same way you can solve equations, by following these&nbsp;rules.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Rules to solve inequalities</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\" style=\"width: 15%;\">\r\n		<p>Rule 1</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">, then&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is less than&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p>Rule 2</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;then&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;</span><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span>.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p>Rule 3</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You may add the same number to both sides of an inequality.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p>Rule 4</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You may multiply or divide both sides of an inequality by any positive number.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p>Rule 5</p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">When you multiply or divide both sides of an inequality by a&nbsp;negative number, reverse the direction of the inequality sign.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Rule 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Regarding multiplying or dividing both sides of an inequality by a negative number, consider the following:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On the number line,&nbsp;the rule of order states&nbsp;that any number on the number line&nbsp;that is to the right of another number, is greater than that number that is to the left of it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Example</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Consider the inequalities <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\PalAa&gt;2\\)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-1\\PalAb &lt;4\\)</span>:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc 3\\)</span> is to the <span class=\"PalAa\">right</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb 2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa {-1}\\)</span> is to the <span class=\"PalAb\">left</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc 3\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb 2\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa {-1}\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAb\">less than</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd4\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc 3\\PalAa&gt;\\PalCb 2\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa {-1}\\PalAb &lt;\\PalCd4\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/50.svg\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Multiplying or dividing by a <span class=\"PalAb\">negative</span> number switches the numbers to the opposite side of the number line relative to zero:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 22%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBc3\\PalAb{\\times-1}=\\PalBc{-3}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 22%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb2\\PalAb{\\times-1}=\\PalCb{-2}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 12%;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 22%;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalBa{-1}\\PalAb{\\times-1}=\\PalBa{1}\\)</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 22%; text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd4\\PalAb{\\times-1}=\\PalCd{-4}\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/322.svg\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The numbers end up on opposite sides of each other:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"width: 50%;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa{-3}\\)</span> is to the <span class=\"PalAb\">left</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb{-2}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc1\\)</span> is to the <span class=\"PalAa\">right</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{-4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa{-3}\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAb\">less than</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCb{-2}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\">&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc1\\)</span> is <span class=\"PalAa\">greater than</span> <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCd{-4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCa{-3}\\PalAb&lt;\\PalCb{-2}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n		<td><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalCc1\\PalAa&gt;\\PalCd{-4}\\)</span></span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Image\">\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/323.svg\"></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p class=\"Definition\">When you multiply or divide both sides of an inequality by a <span class=\"Emphasis_1\">negative</span> number, reverse the direction of the inequality sign.</p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:09','2017-10-11 12:27:09','',NULL),(728,'Rules 3 &amp; 4','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Solving an inequality: Rules 3 and 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You can solve inequalities in the same way you can solve equations, by following these&nbsp;rules.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Rules to solve inequalities</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Style_Steps\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 1</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>, then&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>&nbsp;is less than&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 2</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(a\\)</span>&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span>&nbsp;then&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b\\)</span>&nbsp;is greater than&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(c\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 3</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You may add the same number to both sides of an inequality.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 4</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">You may multiply or divide both sides of an inequality by any positive number.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<th scope=\"row\">\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Rule 5</span></p>\r\n		</th>\r\n		<td>\r\n		<p><span class=\"BodyText\">When you multiply or divide both sides of an inequality by a&nbsp;negative number, reverse the direction of the inequality sign.</span></p>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Rule 3</h3>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Definition\" style=\"