\\Cdp70\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur17\\Tsp297\\Cdp30\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur17\\Tsp120\\Cdp74\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur17\\Tsp500\\Cdp00\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">None of the above</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:10','2017-10-11 12:27:10','',NULL),(817,'How it works 1','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">How compound interest works 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"280\" scrolling=\"no\" src=\"/FBN1502/assets/110.html\" width=\"690\"></iframe></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">After <span class=\"PalAa\">one </span>year he has earned <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 600\\)</span> as <u>interest</u>, which is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur 60.\\)</span> </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">His new <u>principal</u> for the second year is</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(100\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(600 + 10\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(600=110\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(600\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">or</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(1 \\times 600 + \\PalAb{0,10} \\times 600 = \\PalAa{1,10} \\times 600\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\">or</span></td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(600+60=660\\)</span></td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">We can do this calculation in one step with the multiplication</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{110\\% \\times 600 = 1,10 \\times 600 = 660}\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">During the <span class=\"PalAa\">second </span>year he earns <u>interest </u>on his <u>new principal</u> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur660\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">He earns <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10\\%\\)</span> <u>interest</u> on <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur660\\)</span> which is <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur66\\)</span>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">After two years he will have <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(110\\%\\)</span> of <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur660\\)</span>, or </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\PalAa{110\\% \\times 660 = 1,10 \\times 660 = 726}\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:10','2017-10-11 12:27:10','',NULL),(818,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODUwMTAyMzk0ODg1MzU5OCJ9\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:10','2017-12-15 10:34:49','',NULL),(819,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ3MDk0NDI0NDMwNDE2MTQ3NyJ9\" type=\"t