idth=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:11','2017-12-15 10:34:52','',NULL),(922,'Assignment','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:11','2017-10-11 12:27:11','',NULL),(923,'Questions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Assignment 03, Questions 1&nbsp;to&nbsp;5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Submit Assignment 03&nbsp;</span><span class=\"BodyText\">on&nbsp;</span><em class=\"BodyText\">my</em><span class=\"BodyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;The marks will contribute towards&nbsp;your semester mark. &nbsp;You have to obtain the answers for all ten&nbsp;questions of Assignment 03&nbsp;before you&nbsp;submit Assignment 03&nbsp;on&nbsp;</span><em class=\"BodyText\">my</em><span class=\"BodyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;Therefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 03&nbsp;before you can submit it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number:&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">791106</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 8 March 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 1</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>An appliance store knows that if it sells its new gadgets for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur50\\Cdp00\\)</span> each it can sell <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(200\\)</span> per month, and if it&nbsp;sells the same gadgets for <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur40\\Cdp00\\)</span>, it will sell <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(300\\)</span> per month.<br>\r\nLet <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(p\\)</span> represent the price of the gadgets and let&nbsp;<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(n\\)</span> represent the number of gadgets that is sold per month. &nbsp;Assume that the relationship between&nbsp;price&nbsp;and sales is linear and that the sales are dependent on the price of the gadgets. &nbsp;The linear equation you&nbsp;could use to predict sales for other prices, is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10p+n=700\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10p+n=600\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10p-n=700\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(10p-n=200\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">None of the above</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 2</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The slope of the straight line represented by the equation</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(4x+2y=6\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-4\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-2\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(2\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">None of the above</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 3</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The general equation for a straight line is</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y=ax+b\\)</span>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The line that is defined by such an equation where <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(b=\\displaystyle\\frac{1}{2}\\)</span>&nbsp;is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p class=\"Image\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" height=\"450\" scrolling=\"no\" s