odyText\">Unisa. &nbsp;Therefore, you have to complete all the study units applicable to&nbsp;Assignment 05&nbsp;before you can submit it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If possible, print this page so that you do not need to go through the whole study unit again to get to&nbsp;the questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table_Skeleton\" style=\"width:100%;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">First semester</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n	<tr>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: left;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Unique number:&nbsp;<span class=\"BodyText\">787938</span></h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n		<td style=\"text-align: right;\">\r\n		<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Due date: 12 April 2016</h3>\r\n		</td>\r\n	</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 4</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The derivative of the function</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f(x)=2x^{-\\frac{1}{3}}+5\\)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f\'(x)=-\\displaystyle\\frac{2}{3}x^{\\frac{2}{3}}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f\'(x)=\\displaystyle\\frac{5}{3}x^{-\\frac{4}{3}}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f\'(x)=-\\displaystyle\\frac{2}{3}x^{-\\frac{4}{3}}\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(f\'{x}=-\\displaystyle\\frac{2}{3}x^{-\\frac{4}{3}}+5\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">None of the above</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 5</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">If</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y(x)=-7+5x-\\displaystyle\\frac{5}{2}x^2-3x^4\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">then <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(y\'(x)\\)</span> is equal to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-7+5-5x-12x^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5-\\displaystyle\\frac{5}{4}x-12x^2\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(5-5x-12x^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(-7+5x^0-\\displaystyle\\frac{5}{2}x-9x^3\\)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">None of the above</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading3\">Question 6</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">The total marginal daily cost <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(C\'\\)</span> (in rand) of making jackets is</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span class=\"BodyText\"><span class=\"math-tex\">\\(C\'(x)=25-0\\Ndp10x\\)</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">where <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(x\\)</span> represents the number of jackets made. &nbsp;Find <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(C\'(70)\\)</span> and interpret the result.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">When <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(70\\)</span> jackets are made, it will cost <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur18\\Cdp00\\)</span> to produce the <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(71^{\\text{st}}\\)</span> jacket.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">It will cost <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur18\\Cdp00\\)</span> to produce <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(70\\)</span> jackets.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">When <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(18\\)</span> jackets are made, it will cost <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur70\\Cdp00\\)</span> to produce one additional jacket.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">It will cost <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\Cur70\\Cdp00\\)</span> to produce <span class=\"math-tex\">\\(18\\)</span> jackets.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">None of the above.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:12','2017-10-11 12:27:12','',NULL),(1025,'Learning objectives','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Learning objectives</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">Marginal profit is an application of differentiation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">On completion of this learning unit you should know and be able to:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"BodyText\">\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">determine the marginal profit at a specific production level</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"Bullet_List_2\">interpret&nbsp;the marginal profit at a specific production level</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span class=\"BodyText\">This learning unit includes activities, a video, an exercise and assignment questions.</span></p>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:12','2017-10-11 12:27:12','',NULL),(1026,'Profit','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Profit</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:12','2017-10-11 12:27:12','',NULL),(1027,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://dev.unisaonline.net/e-content/tao-client/show?launch_url=https://dev.unisaonline.net/tao/ltiDeliveryProvider/DeliveryTool/launch/eyJkZWxpdmVyeSI6Imh0dHA6XC9cL3VuaXNhdGVzdDIuY2xvdWRhcHAubmV0XC90YW9cL3VuaXNhLnJkZiNpMTQ2ODU2NDI4MDkzMTU0NDQ4In0=\" type=\"text/html\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800px\"></iframe></div>','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:12','2017-12-15 10:34:55','',NULL),(1028,'Marginal profit','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Marginal profit</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:12','2017-10-11 12:27:12','',NULL),(1029,'Marginal functions','\r\n<h3 class=\"Heading2\">Marginal functions</h3>\r\n\r\n','',1,1,'2017-10-11 12:27:12','2017-10-11 12:27:12','',NULL),(1030,'Activity','<div class=\"iframeCover\"><iframe allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"ckeditorframe\" scrolling=\"yes\" frameborder=\"0\" src=\